var book = {
	"name": "2 Kings",
	"numChapters": 25,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>After Ahab’s death, Moab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9535A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9535A\"></sup> rebelled against Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Ahaziah had fallen through the lattice of his upper room in Samaria and injured himself. So he sent messengers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9536B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9536B\"></sup> saying to them, “Go and consult Baal-Zebub,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9536C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9536C\"></sup> the god of Ekron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9536D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9536D\"></sup> to see if I will recover<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9536E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9536E\"></sup> from this injury.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9537F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9537F\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Elijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9537G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9537G\"></sup> the Tishbite, “Go up and meet the messengers of the king of Samaria and ask them, ‘Is it because there is no God in Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9537H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9537H\"></sup> that you are going off to consult Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron?’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Therefore this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘You will not leave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9538I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9538I\"></sup> the bed you are lying on. You will certainly die!’” So Elijah went.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the messengers returned to the king, he asked them, “Why have you come back?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“A man came to meet us,” they replied. “And he said to us, ‘Go back to the king who sent you and tell him, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: Is it because there is no God in Israel that you are sending messengers to consult Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron? Therefore you will not leave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9540J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9540J\"></sup> the bed you are lying on. You will certainly die!”’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king asked them, “What kind of man was it who came to meet you and told you this?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They replied, “He had a garment of hair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9542K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9542K\"></sup> and had a leather belt around his waist.”The king said, “That was Elijah the Tishbite.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he sent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9543L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9543L\"></sup> to Elijah a captain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9543M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9543M\"></sup> with his company of fifty men. The captain went up to Elijah, who was sitting on the top of a hill, and said to him, “Man of God, the king says, ‘Come down!’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Elijah answered the captain, “If I am a man of God, may fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty men!” Then fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9544N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9544N\"></sup> fell from heaven and consumed the captain and his men.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>At this the king sent to Elijah another captain with his fifty men. The captain said to him, “Man of God, this is what the king says, ‘Come down at once!’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“If I am a man of God,” Elijah replied, “may fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty men!” Then the fire of God fell from heaven and consumed him and his fifty men.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the king sent a third captain with his fifty men. This third captain went up and fell on his knees before Elijah. “Man of God,” he begged, “please have respect for my life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9547O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9547O\"></sup> and the lives of these fifty men, your servants!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>See, fire has fallen from heaven and consumed the first two captains and all their men. But now have respect for my life!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9549P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9549P\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Elijah, “Go down with him; do not be afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9549Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9549Q\"></sup> of him.” So Elijah got up and went down with him to the king.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He told the king, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: Is it because there is no God in Israel for you to consult that you have sent messengers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9550R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9550R\"></sup> to consult Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron? Because you have done this, you will never leave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9550S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9550S\"></sup> the bed you are lying on. You will certainly die!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he died,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9551T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9551T\"></sup> according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that Elijah had spoken.Because Ahaziah had no son, Joram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9551U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9551U\"></sup> succeeded him as king in the second year of Jehoram son of Jehoshaphat king of Judah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As for all the other events of Ahaziah’s reign, and what he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel?"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was about to take<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9553A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9553A\"></sup> Elijah up to heaven in a whirlwind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9553B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9553B\"></sup> Elijah and Elisha<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9553C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9553C\"></sup> were on their way from Gilgal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9553D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9553D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Elijah said to Elisha, “Stay here;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9554E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9554E\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me to Bethel.”But Elisha said, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as you live, I will not leave you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9554F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9554F\"></sup> So they went down to Bethel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The company<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9555G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9555G\"></sup> of the prophets at Bethel came out to Elisha and asked, “Do you know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is going to take your master from you today?”“Yes, I know,” Elisha replied, “so be quiet.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Elijah said to him, “Stay here, Elisha; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me to Jericho.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9556H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9556H\"></sup>”And he replied, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as you live, I will not leave you.” So they went to Jericho.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The company<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9557I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9557I\"></sup> of the prophets at Jericho went up to Elisha and asked him, “Do you know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is going to take your master from you today?”“Yes, I know,” he replied, “so be quiet.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Elijah said to him, “Stay here;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9558J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9558J\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent me to the Jordan.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9558K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9558K\"></sup>And he replied, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as you live, I will not leave you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9558L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9558L\"></sup> So the two of them walked on.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Fifty men from the company of the prophets went and stood at a distance, facing the place where Elijah and Elisha had stopped at the Jordan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Elijah took his cloak,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9560M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9560M\"></sup> rolled it up and struck<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9560N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9560N\"></sup> the water with it. The water divided<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9560O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9560O\"></sup> to the right and to the left, and the two of them crossed over on dry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9560P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9560P\"></sup> ground.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they had crossed, Elijah said to Elisha, “Tell me, what can I do for you before I am taken from you?”“Let me inherit a double<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9561Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9561Q\"></sup> portion of your spirit,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9561R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9561R\"></sup> Elisha replied.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“You have asked a difficult thing,” Elijah said, “yet if you see me when I am taken from you, it will be yours—otherwise, it will not.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As they were walking along and talking together, suddenly a chariot of fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9563S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9563S\"></sup> and horses of fire appeared and separated the two of them, and Elijah went up to heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9563T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9563T\"></sup> in a whirlwind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9563U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9563U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Elisha saw this and cried out, “My father! My father! The chariots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9564V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9564V\"></sup> and horsemen of Israel!” And Elisha saw him no more. Then he took hold of his garment and tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9564W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9564W\"></sup> it in two.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Elisha then picked up Elijah’s cloak that had fallen from him and went back and stood on the bank of the Jordan.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He took the cloak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9566X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9566X\"></sup> that had fallen from Elijah and struck<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9566Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9566Y\"></sup> the water with it. “Where now is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Elijah?” he asked. When he struck the water, it divided to the right and to the left, and he crossed over.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The company<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9567Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9567Z\"></sup> of the prophets from Jericho, who were watching, said, “The spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9567AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9567AA\"></sup> of Elijah is resting on Elisha.” And they went to meet him and bowed to the ground before him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Look,” they said, “we your servants have fifty able men. Let them go and look for your master. Perhaps the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9568AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9568AB\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has picked him up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9568AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9568AC\"></sup> and set him down on some mountain or in some valley.”“No,” Elisha replied, “do not send them.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But they persisted until he was too embarrassed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9569AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9569AD\"></sup> to refuse. So he said, “Send them.” And they sent fifty men, who searched for three days but did not find him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they returned to Elisha, who was staying in Jericho, he said to them, “Didn’t I tell you not to go?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The people of the city said to Elisha, “Look, our lord, this town is well situated, as you can see, but the water is bad and the land is unproductive.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Bring me a new bowl,” he said, “and put salt in it.” So they brought it to him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then he went out to the spring and threw<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9573AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9573AE\"></sup> the salt into it, saying, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘I have healed this water. Never again will it cause death or make the land unproductive.’”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the water has remained pure<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9574AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9574AF\"></sup> to this day, according to the word Elisha had spoken.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>From there Elisha went up to Bethel. As he was walking along the road, some boys came out of the town and jeered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9575AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9575AG\"></sup> at him. “Get out of here, baldy!” they said. “Get out of here, baldy!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He turned around, looked at them and called down a curse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9576AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9576AH\"></sup> on them in the name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9576AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9576AI\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then two bears came out of the woods and mauled forty-two of the boys.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And he went on to Mount Carmel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9577AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9577AJ\"></sup> and from there returned to Samaria."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Joram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9578A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9578A\"></sup> son of Ahab became king of Israel in Samaria in the eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and he reigned twelve years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9579B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9579B\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but not as his father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9579C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9579C\"></sup> and mother had done. He got rid of the sacred stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9579D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9579D\"></sup> of Baal that his father had made.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Nevertheless he clung to the sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9580E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9580E\"></sup> of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit; he did not turn away from them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now Mesha king of Moab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9581F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9581F\"></sup> raised sheep, and he had to pay the king of Israel a tribute of a hundred thousand lambs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9581G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9581G\"></sup> and the wool of a hundred thousand rams.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But after Ahab died, the king of Moab rebelled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9582H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9582H\"></sup> against the king of Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So at that time King Joram set out from Samaria and mobilized all Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He also sent this message to Jehoshaphat king of Judah: “The king of Moab has rebelled against me. Will you go with me to fight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9584I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9584I\"></sup> against Moab?”“I will go with you,” he replied. “I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“By what route shall we attack?” he asked.“Through the Desert of Edom,” he answered.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the king of Israel set out with the king of Judah and the king of Edom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9586J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9586J\"></sup> After a roundabout march of seven days, the army had no more water for themselves or for the animals with them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“What!” exclaimed the king of Israel. “Has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called us three kings together only to deliver us into the hands of Moab?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Jehoshaphat asked, “Is there no prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> here, through whom we may inquire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9588K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9588K\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”An officer of the king of Israel answered, “Elisha<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9588L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9588L\"></sup> son of Shaphat is here. He used to pour water on the hands of Elijah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9588M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9588M\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jehoshaphat said, “The word<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9589N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9589N\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with him.” So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat and the king of Edom went down to him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Elisha said to the king of Israel, “Why do you want to involve me? Go to the prophets of your father and the prophets of your mother.”“No,” the king of Israel answered, “because it was the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who called us three kings together to deliver us into the hands of Moab.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Elisha said, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty lives, whom I serve, if I did not have respect for the presence of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, I would not pay any attention to you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But now bring me a harpist.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9592O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9592O\"></sup>While the harpist was playing, the hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9592P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9592P\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came on Elisha",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and he said, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: I will fill this valley with pools of water.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: You will see neither wind nor rain, yet this valley will be filled with water,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9594Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9594Q\"></sup> and you, your cattle and your other animals will drink.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>This is an easy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9595R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9595R\"></sup> thing in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; he will also deliver Moab into your hands.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You will overthrow every fortified city and every major town. You will cut down every good tree, stop up all the springs, and ruin every good field with stones.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The next morning, about the time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9597S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9597S\"></sup> for offering the sacrifice, there it was—water flowing from the direction of Edom! And the land was filled with water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9597T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9597T\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now all the Moabites had heard that the kings had come to fight against them; so every man, young and old, who could bear arms was called up and stationed on the border.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When they got up early in the morning, the sun was shining on the water. To the Moabites across the way, the water looked red—like blood.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“That’s blood!” they said. “Those kings must have fought and slaughtered each other. Now to the plunder, Moab!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But when the Moabites came to the camp of Israel, the Israelites rose up and fought them until they fled. And the Israelites invaded the land and slaughtered the Moabites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They destroyed the towns, and each man threw a stone on every good field until it was covered. They stopped up all the springs and cut down every good tree. Only Kir Hareseth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9602U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9602U\"></sup> was left with its stones in place, but men armed with slings surrounded it and attacked it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When the king of Moab saw that the battle had gone against him, he took with him seven hundred swordsmen to break through to the king of Edom, but they failed.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then he took his firstborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9604V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9604V\"></sup> son, who was to succeed him as king, and offered him as a sacrifice on the city wall. The fury against Israel was great; they withdrew and returned to their own land."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>The wife of a man from the company<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9605A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9605A\"></sup> of the prophets cried out to Elisha, “Your servant my husband is dead, and you know that he revered the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. But now his creditor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9605B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9605B\"></sup> is coming to take my two boys as his slaves.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Elisha replied to her, “How can I help you? Tell me, what do you have in your house?”“Your servant has nothing there at all,” she said, “except a small jar of olive oil.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9606C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9606C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Elisha said, “Go around and ask all your neighbors for empty jars. Don’t ask for just a few.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then go inside and shut the door behind you and your sons. Pour oil into all the jars, and as each is filled, put it to one side.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>She left him and shut the door behind her and her sons. They brought the jars to her and she kept pouring.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When all the jars were full, she said to her son, “Bring me another one.”But he replied, “There is not a jar left.” Then the oil stopped flowing.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>She went and told the man of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9611D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9611D\"></sup> and he said, “Go, sell the oil and pay your debts. You and your sons can live on what is left.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>One day Elisha went to Shunem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9612E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9612E\"></sup> And a well-to-do woman was there, who urged him to stay for a meal. So whenever he came by, he stopped there to eat.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>She said to her husband, “I know that this man who often comes our way is a holy man of God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Let’s make a small room on the roof and put in it a bed and a table, a chair and a lamp for him. Then he can stay<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9614F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9614F\"></sup> there whenever he comes to us.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>One day when Elisha came, he went up to his room and lay down there.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said to his servant Gehazi, “Call the Shunammite.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9616G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9616G\"></sup> So he called her, and she stood before him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Elisha said to him, “Tell her, ‘You have gone to all this trouble for us. Now what can be done for you? Can we speak on your behalf to the king or the commander of the army?’”She replied, “I have a home among my own people.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“What can be done for her?” Elisha asked.Gehazi said, “She has no son, and her husband is old.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Elisha said, “Call her.” So he called her, and she stood in the doorway.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“About this time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9620H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9620H\"></sup> next year,” Elisha said, “you will hold a son in your arms.”“No, my lord!” she objected. “Please, man of God, don’t mislead your servant!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the woman became pregnant, and the next year about that same time she gave birth to a son, just as Elisha had told her.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The child grew, and one day he went out to his father, who was with the reapers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9622I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9622I\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He said to his father, “My head! My head!”His father told a servant, “Carry him to his mother.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After the servant had lifted him up and carried him to his mother, the boy sat on her lap until noon, and then he died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>She went up and laid him on the bed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9625J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9625J\"></sup> of the man of God, then shut the door and went out.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>She called her husband and said, “Please send me one of the servants and a donkey so I can go to the man of God quickly and return.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Why go to him today?” he asked. “It’s not the New Moon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9627K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9627K\"></sup> or the Sabbath.”“That’s all right,” she said.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She saddled the donkey and said to her servant, “Lead on; don’t slow down for me unless I tell you.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So she set out and came to the man of God at Mount Carmel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9629L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9629L\"></sup>When he saw her in the distance, the man of God said to his servant Gehazi, “Look! There’s the Shunammite!",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Run to meet her and ask her, ‘Are you all right? Is your husband all right? Is your child all right?’”“Everything is all right,” she said.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When she reached the man of God at the mountain, she took hold of his feet. Gehazi came over to push her away, but the man of God said, “Leave her alone! She is in bitter distress,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9631M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9631M\"></sup> but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has hidden it from me and has not told me why.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Did I ask you for a son, my lord?” she said. “Didn’t I tell you, ‘Don’t raise my hopes’?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Elisha said to Gehazi, “Tuck your cloak into your belt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9633N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9633N\"></sup> take my staff<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9633O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9633O\"></sup> in your hand and run. Don’t greet anyone you meet, and if anyone greets you, do not answer. Lay my staff on the boy’s face.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But the child’s mother said, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives and as you live, I will not leave you.” So he got up and followed her.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Gehazi went on ahead and laid the staff on the boy’s face, but there was no sound or response. So Gehazi went back to meet Elisha and told him, “The boy has not awakened.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When Elisha reached the house, there was the boy lying dead on his couch.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9636P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9636P\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He went in, shut the door on the two of them and prayed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9637Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9637Q\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then he got on the bed and lay on the boy, mouth to mouth, eyes to eyes, hands to hands. As he stretched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9638R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9638R\"></sup> himself out on him, the boy’s body grew warm.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Elisha turned away and walked back and forth in the room and then got on the bed and stretched out on him once more. The boy sneezed seven times<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9639S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9639S\"></sup> and opened his eyes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9639T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9639T\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Elisha summoned Gehazi and said, “Call the Shunammite.” And he did. When she came, he said, “Take your son.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9640U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9640U\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>She came in, fell at his feet and bowed to the ground. Then she took her son and went out.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Elisha returned to Gilgal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9642V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9642V\"></sup> and there was a famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9642W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9642W\"></sup> in that region. While the company of the prophets was meeting with him, he said to his servant, “Put on the large pot and cook some stew for these prophets.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>One of them went out into the fields to gather herbs and found a wild vine and picked as many of its gourds as his garment could hold. When he returned, he cut them up into the pot of stew, though no one knew what they were.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The stew was poured out for the men, but as they began to eat it, they cried out, “Man of God, there is death in the pot!” And they could not eat it.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Elisha said, “Get some flour.” He put it into the pot and said, “Serve it to the people to eat.” And there was nothing harmful in the pot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9645X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9645X\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>A man came from Baal Shalishah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9646Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9646Y\"></sup> bringing the man of God twenty loaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9646Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9646Z\"></sup> of barley bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9646AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9646AA\"></sup> baked from the first ripe grain, along with some heads of new grain. “Give it to the people to eat,” Elisha said.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“How can I set this before a hundred men?” his servant asked.But Elisha answered, “Give it to the people to eat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9647AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9647AB\"></sup> For this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘They will eat and have some left over.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9647AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9647AC\"></sup>’”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Then he set it before them, and they ate and had some left over, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now Naaman was commander of the army of the king of Aram.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9649A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9649A\"></sup> He was a great man in the sight of his master and highly regarded, because through him the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given victory to Aram. He was a valiant soldier, but he had leprosy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9649B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9649B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now bands of raiders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9650C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9650C\"></sup> from Aram had gone out and had taken captive a young girl from Israel, and she served Naaman’s wife.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>She said to her mistress, “If only my master would see the prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9651D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9651D\"></sup> who is in Samaria! He would cure him of his leprosy.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Naaman went to his master and told him what the girl from Israel had said.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“By all means, go,” the king of Aram replied. “I will send a letter to the king of Israel.” So Naaman left, taking with him ten talents of silver, six thousand shekels of gold and ten sets of clothing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9653E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9653E\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The letter that he took to the king of Israel read: “With this letter I am sending my servant Naaman to you so that you may cure him of his leprosy.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As soon as the king of Israel read the letter,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9655F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9655F\"></sup> he tore his robes and said, “Am I God?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9655G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9655G\"></sup> Can I kill and bring back to life?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9655H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9655H\"></sup> Why does this fellow send someone to me to be cured of his leprosy? See how he is trying to pick a quarrel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9655I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9655I\"></sup> with me!”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Elisha the man of God heard that the king of Israel had torn his robes, he sent him this message: “Why have you torn your robes? Have the man come to me and he will know that there is a prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9656J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9656J\"></sup> in Israel.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Naaman went with his horses and chariots and stopped at the door of Elisha’s house.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Elisha sent a messenger to say to him, “Go, wash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9658K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9658K\"></sup> yourself seven times<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9658L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9658L\"></sup> in the Jordan, and your flesh will be restored and you will be cleansed.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Naaman went away angry and said, “I thought that he would surely come out to me and stand and call on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, wave his hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9659M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9659M\"></sup> over the spot and cure me of my leprosy.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Are not Abana and Pharpar, the rivers of Damascus, better than all the waters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9660N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9660N\"></sup> of Israel? Couldn’t I wash in them and be cleansed?” So he turned and went off in a rage.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9660O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9660O\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Naaman’s servants went to him and said, “My father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9661P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9661P\"></sup> if the prophet had told you to do some great thing, would you not have done it? How much more, then, when he tells you, ‘Wash and be cleansed’!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he went down and dipped himself in the Jordan seven times,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9662Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9662Q\"></sup> as the man of God had told him, and his flesh was restored<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9662R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9662R\"></sup> and became clean like that of a young boy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9662S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9662S\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Naaman and all his attendants went back to the man of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9663T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9663T\"></sup>. He stood before him and said, “Now I know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9663U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9663U\"></sup> that there is no God in all the world except in Israel. So please accept a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9663V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9663V\"></sup> from your servant.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The prophet answered, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, whom I serve, I will not accept a thing.” And even though Naaman urged him, he refused.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9664W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9664W\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“If you will not,” said Naaman, “please let me, your servant, be given as much earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9665X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9665X\"></sup> as a pair of mules can carry, for your servant will never again make burnt offerings and sacrifices to any other god but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forgive your servant for this one thing: When my master enters the temple of Rimmon to bow down and he is leaning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9666Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9666Y\"></sup> on my arm and I have to bow there also—when I bow down in the temple of Rimmon, may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forgive your servant for this.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Go in peace,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9667Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9667Z\"></sup> Elisha said.After Naaman had traveled some distance,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Gehazi, the servant of Elisha the man of God, said to himself, “My master was too easy on Naaman, this Aramean, by not accepting from him what he brought. As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9668AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9668AA\"></sup> lives, I will run after him and get something from him.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Gehazi hurried after Naaman. When Naaman saw him running toward him, he got down from the chariot to meet him. “Is everything all right?” he asked.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Everything is all right,” Gehazi answered. “My master sent me to say, ‘Two young men from the company of the prophets have just come to me from the hill country of Ephraim. Please give them a talent of silver and two sets of clothing.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9670AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9670AB\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“By all means, take two talents,” said Naaman. He urged Gehazi to accept them, and then tied up the two talents of silver in two bags, with two sets of clothing. He gave them to two of his servants, and they carried them ahead of Gehazi.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Gehazi came to the hill, he took the things from the servants and put them away in the house. He sent the men away and they left.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When he went in and stood before his master, Elisha asked him, “Where have you been, Gehazi?”“Your servant didn’t go anywhere,” Gehazi answered.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Elisha said to him, “Was not my spirit with you when the man got down from his chariot to meet you? Is this the time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9674AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9674AC\"></sup> to take money or to accept clothes—or olive groves and vineyards, or flocks and herds, or male and female slaves?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9674AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9674AD\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Naaman’s leprosy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9675AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9675AE\"></sup> will cling to you and to your descendants forever.” Then Gehazi<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9675AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9675AF\"></sup> went from Elisha’s presence and his skin was leprous—it had become as white as snow.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9675AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9675AG\"></sup>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>The company<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9676A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9676A\"></sup> of the prophets said to Elisha, “Look, the place where we meet with you is too small for us.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Let us go to the Jordan, where each of us can get a pole; and let us build a place there for us to meet.”And he said, “Go.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then one of them said, “Won’t you please come with your servants?”“I will,” Elisha replied.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he went with them.They went to the Jordan and began to cut down trees.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As one of them was cutting down a tree, the iron axhead fell into the water. “Oh no, my lord!” he cried out. “It was borrowed!”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The man of God asked, “Where did it fall?” When he showed him the place, Elisha cut a stick and threw<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9681B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9681B\"></sup> it there, and made the iron float.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Lift it out,” he said. Then the man reached out his hand and took it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now the king of Aram was at war with Israel. After conferring with his officers, he said, “I will set up my camp in such and such a place.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The man of God sent word to the king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9684C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9684C\"></sup> of Israel: “Beware of passing that place, because the Arameans are going down there.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the king of Israel checked on the place indicated by the man of God. Time and again Elisha warned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9685D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9685D\"></sup> the king, so that he was on his guard in such places.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>This enraged the king of Aram. He summoned his officers and demanded of them, “Tell me! Which of us is on the side of the king of Israel?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“None of us, my lord the king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9687E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9687E\"></sup>,” said one of his officers, “but Elisha, the prophet who is in Israel, tells the king of Israel the very words you speak in your bedroom.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Go, find out where he is,” the king ordered, “so I can send men and capture him.” The report came back: “He is in Dothan.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9688F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9688F\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he sent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9689G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9689G\"></sup> horses and chariots and a strong force there. They went by night and surrounded the city.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the servant of the man of God got up and went out early the next morning, an army with horses and chariots had surrounded the city. “Oh no, my lord! What shall we do?” the servant asked.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Don’t be afraid,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9691H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9691H\"></sup> the prophet answered. “Those who are with us are more<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9691I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9691I\"></sup> than those who are with them.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Elisha prayed, “Open his eyes, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so that he may see.” Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> opened the servant’s eyes, and he looked and saw the hills full of horses and chariots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9692J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9692J\"></sup> of fire all around Elisha.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As the enemy came down toward him, Elisha prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Strike this army with blindness.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9693K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9693K\"></sup> So he struck them with blindness, as Elisha had asked.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Elisha told them, “This is not the road and this is not the city. Follow me, and I will lead you to the man you are looking for.” And he led them to Samaria.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After they entered the city, Elisha said, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, open the eyes of these men so they can see.” Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> opened their eyes and they looked, and there they were, inside Samaria.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When the king of Israel saw them, he asked Elisha, “Shall I kill them, my father?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9696L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9696L\"></sup> Shall I kill them?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Do not kill them,” he answered. “Would you kill those you have captured<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9697M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9697M\"></sup> with your own sword or bow? Set food and water before them so that they may eat and drink and then go back to their master.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So he prepared a great feast for them, and after they had finished eating and drinking, he sent them away, and they returned to their master. So the bands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9698N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9698N\"></sup> from Aram stopped raiding Israel’s territory.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Some time later, Ben-Hadad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9699O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9699O\"></sup> king of Aram mobilized his entire army and marched up and laid siege<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9699P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9699P\"></sup> to Samaria.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>There was a great famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9700Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9700Q\"></sup> in the city; the siege lasted so long that a donkey’s head sold for eighty shekels of silver, and a quarter of a cab of seed pods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9700R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9700R\"></sup> for five shekels.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>As the king of Israel was passing by on the wall, a woman cried to him, “Help me, my lord the king!”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The king replied, “If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> does not help you, where can I get help for you? From the threshing floor? From the winepress?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he asked her, “What’s the matter?”She answered, “This woman said to me, ‘Give up your son so we may eat him today, and tomorrow we’ll eat my son.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So we cooked my son and ate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9704S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9704S\"></sup> him. The next day I said to her, ‘Give up your son so we may eat him,’ but she had hidden him.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When the king heard the woman’s words, he tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9705T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9705T\"></sup> his robes. As he went along the wall, the people looked, and they saw that, under his robes, he had sackcloth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9705U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9705U\"></sup> on his body.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He said, “May God deal with me, be it ever so severely, if the head of Elisha son of Shaphat remains on his shoulders today!”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now Elisha was sitting in his house, and the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9707V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9707V\"></sup> were sitting with him. The king sent a messenger ahead, but before he arrived, Elisha said to the elders, “Don’t you see how this murderer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9707W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9707W\"></sup> is sending someone to cut off my head?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9707X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9707X\"></sup> Look, when the messenger comes, shut the door and hold it shut against him. Is not the sound of his master’s footsteps behind him?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>While he was still talking to them, the messenger came down to him.The king said, “This disaster is from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Why should I wait<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9708Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9708Y\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> any longer?”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Elisha replied, “Hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: About this time tomorrow, a seah of the finest flour will sell for a shekel and two seahs of barley for a shekel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9709A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9709A\"></sup> at the gate of Samaria.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The officer on whose arm the king was leaning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9710B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9710B\"></sup> said to the man of God, “Look, even if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should open the floodgates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9710C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9710C\"></sup> of the heavens, could this happen?”“You will see it with your own eyes,” answered Elisha, “but you will not eat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9710D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9710D\"></sup> any of it!”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now there were four men with leprosy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9711E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9711E\"></sup> at the entrance of the city gate. They said to each other, “Why stay here until we die?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If we say, ‘We’ll go into the city’—the famine is there, and we will die. And if we stay here, we will die. So let’s go over to the camp of the Arameans and surrender. If they spare us, we live; if they kill us, then we die.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>At dusk they got up and went to the camp of the Arameans. When they reached the edge of the camp, no one was there,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>for the Lord had caused the Arameans to hear the sound<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9714F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9714F\"></sup> of chariots and horses and a great army, so that they said to one another, “Look, the king of Israel has hired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9714G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9714G\"></sup> the Hittite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9714H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9714H\"></sup> and Egyptian kings to attack us!”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So they got up and fled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9715I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9715I\"></sup> in the dusk and abandoned their tents and their horses and donkeys. They left the camp as it was and ran for their lives.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The men who had leprosy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9716J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9716J\"></sup> reached the edge of the camp, entered one of the tents and ate and drank. Then they took silver, gold and clothes, and went off and hid them. They returned and entered another tent and took some things from it and hid them also.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then they said to each other, “What we’re doing is not right. This is a day of good news and we are keeping it to ourselves. If we wait until daylight, punishment will overtake us. Let’s go at once and report this to the royal palace.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they went and called out to the city gatekeepers and told them, “We went into the Aramean camp and no one was there—not a sound of anyone—only tethered horses and donkeys, and the tents left just as they were.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The gatekeepers shouted the news, and it was reported within the palace.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The king got up in the night and said to his officers, “I will tell you what the Arameans have done to us. They know we are starving; so they have left the camp to hide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9720K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9720K\"></sup> in the countryside, thinking, ‘They will surely come out, and then we will take them alive and get into the city.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>One of his officers answered, “Have some men take five of the horses that are left in the city. Their plight will be like that of all the Israelites left here—yes, they will only be like all these Israelites who are doomed. So let us send them to find out what happened.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So they selected two chariots with their horses, and the king sent them after the Aramean army. He commanded the drivers, “Go and find out what has happened.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They followed them as far as the Jordan, and they found the whole road strewn with the clothing and equipment the Arameans had thrown away in their headlong flight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9723L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9723L\"></sup> So the messengers returned and reported to the king.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the people went out and plundered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9724M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9724M\"></sup> the camp of the Arameans. So a seah of the finest flour sold for a shekel, and two seahs of barley sold for a shekel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9724N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9724N\"></sup> as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the king had put the officer on whose arm he leaned in charge of the gate, and the people trampled him in the gateway, and he died,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9725O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9725O\"></sup> just as the man of God had foretold when the king came down to his house.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It happened as the man of God had said to the king: “About this time tomorrow, a seah of the finest flour will sell for a shekel and two seahs of barley for a shekel at the gate of Samaria.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The officer had said to the man of God, “Look, even if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should open the floodgates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9727P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9727P\"></sup> of the heavens, could this happen?” The man of God had replied, “You will see it with your own eyes, but you will not eat any of it!”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And that is exactly what happened to him, for the people trampled him in the gateway, and he died."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Now Elisha had said to the woman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9729A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9729A\"></sup> whose son he had restored to life, “Go away with your family and stay for a while wherever you can, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has decreed a famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9729B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9729B\"></sup> in the land that will last seven years.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9729C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9729C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The woman proceeded to do as the man of God said. She and her family went away and stayed in the land of the Philistines seven years.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>At the end of the seven years she came back from the land of the Philistines and went to appeal to the king for her house and land.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king was talking to Gehazi, the servant of the man of God, and had said, “Tell me about all the great things Elisha has done.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Just as Gehazi was telling the king how Elisha had restored<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9733D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9733D\"></sup> the dead to life, the woman whose son Elisha had brought back to life came to appeal to the king for her house and land.Gehazi said, “This is the woman, my lord the king, and this is her son whom Elisha restored to life.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The king asked the woman about it, and she told him.Then he assigned an official to her case and said to him, “Give back everything that belonged to her, including all the income from her land from the day she left the country until now.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Elisha went to Damascus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9735E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9735E\"></sup> and Ben-Hadad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9735F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9735F\"></sup> king of Aram was ill. When the king was told, “The man of God has come all the way up here,”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>he said to Hazael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9736G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9736G\"></sup> “Take a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9736H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9736H\"></sup> with you and go to meet the man of God. Consult<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9736I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9736I\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through him; ask him, ‘Will I recover from this illness?’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Hazael went to meet Elisha, taking with him as a gift forty camel-loads of all the finest wares of Damascus. He went in and stood before him, and said, “Your son Ben-Hadad king of Aram has sent me to ask, ‘Will I recover from this illness?’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Elisha answered, “Go and say to him, ‘You will certainly recover.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9738J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9738J\"></sup> Nevertheless, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has revealed to me that he will in fact die.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He stared at him with a fixed gaze until Hazael was embarrassed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9739K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9739K\"></sup> Then the man of God began to weep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9739L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9739L\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Why is my lord weeping?” asked Hazael.“Because I know the harm<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9740M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9740M\"></sup> you will do to the Israelites,” he answered. “You will set fire to their fortified places, kill their young men with the sword, dash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9740N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9740N\"></sup> their little children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9740O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9740O\"></sup> to the ground, and rip open<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9740P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9740P\"></sup> their pregnant women.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hazael said, “How could your servant, a mere dog,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9741Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9741Q\"></sup> accomplish such a feat?”“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has shown me that you will become king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9741R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9741R\"></sup> of Aram,” answered Elisha.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Hazael left Elisha and returned to his master. When Ben-Hadad asked, “What did Elisha say to you?” Hazael replied, “He told me that you would certainly recover.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the next day he took a thick cloth, soaked it in water and spread it over the king’s face, so that he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9743S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9743S\"></sup> Then Hazael succeeded him as king.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>In the fifth year of Joram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9744U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9744U\"></sup> son of Ahab king of Israel, when Jehoshaphat was king of Judah, Jehoram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9744V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9744V\"></sup> son of Jehoshaphat began his reign as king of Judah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eight years.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He followed the ways of the kings of Israel, as the house of Ahab had done, for he married a daughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9746W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9746W\"></sup> of Ahab. He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Nevertheless, for the sake of his servant David, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not willing to destroy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9747X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9747X\"></sup> Judah. He had promised to maintain a lamp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9747Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9747Y\"></sup> for David and his descendants forever.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In the time of Jehoram, Edom rebelled against Judah and set up its own king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9748Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9748Z\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Jehoram went to Zair with all his chariots. The Edomites surrounded him and his chariot commanders, but he rose up and broke through by night; his army, however, fled back home.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>To this day Edom has been in rebellion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9750AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9750AA\"></sup> against Judah. Libnah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9750AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9750AB\"></sup> revolted at the same time.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As for the other events of Jehoram’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Jehoram rested with his ancestors and was buried with them in the City of David. And Ahaziah his son succeeded him as king.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In the twelfth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9753AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9753AD\"></sup> year of Joram son of Ahab king of Israel, Ahaziah son of Jehoram king of Judah began to reign.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ahaziah was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem one year. His mother’s name was Athaliah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9754AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9754AE\"></sup> a granddaughter of Omri<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9754AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9754AF\"></sup> king of Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He followed the ways of the house of Ahab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9755AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9755AG\"></sup> and did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9755AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9755AH\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the house of Ahab had done, for he was related by marriage to Ahab’s family.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ahaziah went with Joram son of Ahab to war against Hazael king of Aram at Ramoth Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9756AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9756AI\"></sup> The Arameans wounded Joram;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>so King Joram returned to Jezreel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9757AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9757AJ\"></sup> to recover from the wounds the Arameans had inflicted on him at Ramoth in his battle with Hazael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9757AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9757AK\"></sup> king of Aram.Then Ahaziah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9757AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9757AL\"></sup> son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to Jezreel to see Joram son of Ahab, because he had been wounded."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>The prophet Elisha summoned a man from the company<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9758A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9758A\"></sup> of the prophets and said to him, “Tuck your cloak into your belt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9758B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9758B\"></sup> take this flask of olive oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9758C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9758C\"></sup> with you and go to Ramoth Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9758D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9758D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When you get there, look for Jehu son of Jehoshaphat, the son of Nimshi. Go to him, get him away from his companions and take him into an inner room.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then take the flask and pour the oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9760E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9760E\"></sup> on his head and declare, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: I anoint you king over Israel.’ Then open the door and run; don’t delay!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the young prophet went to Ramoth Gilead.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When he arrived, he found the army officers sitting together. “I have a message for you, commander,” he said.“For which of us?” asked Jehu.“For you, commander,” he replied.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Jehu got up and went into the house. Then the prophet poured the oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9763F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9763F\"></sup> on Jehu’s head and declared, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: ‘I anoint you king over the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s people Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You are to destroy the house of Ahab your master, and I will avenge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9764G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9764G\"></sup> the blood of my servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9764H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9764H\"></sup> the prophets and the blood of all the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s servants shed by Jezebel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9764I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9764I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The whole house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9765J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9765J\"></sup> of Ahab will perish. I will cut off from Ahab every last male<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9765K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9765K\"></sup> in Israel—slave or free.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I will make the house of Ahab like the house of Jeroboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9766L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9766L\"></sup> son of Nebat and like the house of Baasha<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9766M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9766M\"></sup> son of Ahijah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As for Jezebel, dogs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9767N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9767N\"></sup> will devour her on the plot of ground at Jezreel, and no one will bury her.’” Then he opened the door and ran.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When Jehu went out to his fellow officers, one of them asked him, “Is everything all right? Why did this maniac<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9768O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9768O\"></sup> come to you?”“You know the man and the sort of things he says,” Jehu replied.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“That’s not true!” they said. “Tell us.”Jehu said, “Here is what he told me: ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: I anoint you king over Israel.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They quickly took their cloaks and spread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9770P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9770P\"></sup> them under him on the bare steps. Then they blew the trumpet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9770Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9770Q\"></sup> and shouted, “Jehu is king!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Jehu son of Jehoshaphat, the son of Nimshi, conspired against Joram. (Now Joram and all Israel had been defending Ramoth Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9771S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9771S\"></sup> against Hazael king of Aram,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>but King Joram had returned to Jezreel to recover<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9772T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9772T\"></sup> from the wounds the Arameans had inflicted on him in the battle with Hazael king of Aram.) Jehu said, “If you desire to make me king, don’t let anyone slip out of the city to go and tell the news in Jezreel.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then he got into his chariot and rode to Jezreel, because Joram was resting there and Ahaziah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9773U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9773U\"></sup> king of Judah had gone down to see him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When the lookout<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9774V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9774V\"></sup> standing on the tower in Jezreel saw Jehu’s troops approaching, he called out, “I see some troops coming.”“Get a horseman,” Joram ordered. “Send him to meet them and ask, ‘Do you come in peace?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9774W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9774W\"></sup>’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The horseman rode off to meet Jehu and said, “This is what the king says: ‘Do you come in peace?’”“What do you have to do with peace?” Jehu replied. “Fall in behind me.”The lookout reported, “The messenger has reached them, but he isn’t coming back.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So the king sent out a second horseman. When he came to them he said, “This is what the king says: ‘Do you come in peace?’”Jehu replied, “What do you have to do with peace? Fall in behind me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The lookout reported, “He has reached them, but he isn’t coming back either. The driving is like<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9777X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9777X\"></sup> that of Jehu son of Nimshi—he drives like a maniac.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Hitch up my chariot,” Joram ordered. And when it was hitched up, Joram king of Israel and Ahaziah king of Judah rode out, each in his own chariot, to meet Jehu. They met him at the plot of ground that had belonged to Naboth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9778Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9778Y\"></sup> the Jezreelite.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When Joram saw Jehu he asked, “Have you come in peace, Jehu?”“How can there be peace,” Jehu replied, “as long as all the idolatry and witchcraft of your mother Jezebel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9779Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9779Z\"></sup> abound?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Joram turned about and fled, calling out to Ahaziah, “Treachery,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9780AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9780AA\"></sup> Ahaziah!”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Jehu drew his bow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9781AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9781AB\"></sup> and shot Joram between the shoulders. The arrow pierced his heart and he slumped down in his chariot.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Jehu said to Bidkar, his chariot officer, “Pick him up and throw him on the field that belonged to Naboth the Jezreelite. Remember how you and I were riding together in chariots behind Ahab his father when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke this prophecy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9782AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9782AC\"></sup> against him:",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>‘Yesterday I saw the blood of Naboth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9783AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9783AD\"></sup> and the blood of his sons, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and I will surely make you pay for it on this plot of ground, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’ Now then, pick him up and throw him on that plot, in accordance with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9783AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9783AE\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When Ahaziah king of Judah saw what had happened, he fled up the road to Beth Haggan. Jehu chased him, shouting, “Kill him too!” They wounded him in his chariot on the way up to Gur near Ibleam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9784AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9784AF\"></sup> but he escaped to Megiddo<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9784AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9784AG\"></sup> and died there.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>His servants took him by chariot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9785AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9785AH\"></sup> to Jerusalem and buried him with his ancestors in his tomb in the City of David.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>(In the eleventh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9786AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9786AI\"></sup> year of Joram son of Ahab, Ahaziah had become king of Judah.)",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Jehu went to Jezreel. When Jezebel heard about it, she put on eye makeup,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9787AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9787AJ\"></sup> arranged her hair and looked out of a window.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As Jehu entered the gate, she asked, “Have you come in peace, you Zimri,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9788AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9788AK\"></sup> you murderer of your master?”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He looked up at the window and called out, “Who is on my side? Who?” Two or three eunuchs looked down at him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“Throw her down!” Jehu said. So they threw her down, and some of her blood spattered the wall and the horses as they trampled her underfoot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9790AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9790AL\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jehu went in and ate and drank. “Take care of that cursed woman,” he said, “and bury her, for she was a king’s daughter.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9791AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9791AM\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But when they went out to bury her, they found nothing except her skull, her feet and her hands.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>They went back and told Jehu, who said, “This is the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he spoke through his servant Elijah the Tishbite: On the plot of ground at Jezreel dogs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9793AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9793AN\"></sup> will devour Jezebel’s flesh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9793AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9793AO\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Jezebel’s body will be like dung<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9794AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9794AP\"></sup> on the ground in the plot at Jezreel, so that no one will be able to say, ‘This is Jezebel.’”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now there were in Samaria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9795A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9795A\"></sup> seventy sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9795B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9795B\"></sup> of the house of Ahab. So Jehu wrote letters and sent them to Samaria: to the officials of Jezreel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9795C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9795C\"></sup> to the elders and to the guardians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9795D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9795D\"></sup> of Ahab’s children. He said,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“You have your master’s sons with you and you have chariots and horses, a fortified city and weapons. Now as soon as this letter reaches you,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>choose the best and most worthy of your master’s sons and set him on his father’s throne. Then fight for your master’s house.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But they were terrified and said, “If two kings could not resist him, how can we?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the palace administrator, the city governor, the elders and the guardians sent this message to Jehu: “We are your servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9799E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9799E\"></sup> and we will do anything you say. We will not appoint anyone as king; you do whatever you think best.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Jehu wrote them a second letter, saying, “If you are on my side and will obey me, take the heads of your master’s sons and come to me in Jezreel by this time tomorrow.”Now the royal princes, seventy of them, were with the leading men of the city, who were rearing them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the letter arrived, these men took the princes and slaughtered all seventy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9801F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9801F\"></sup> of them. They put their heads<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9801G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9801G\"></sup> in baskets and sent them to Jehu in Jezreel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the messenger arrived, he told Jehu, “They have brought the heads of the princes.”Then Jehu ordered, “Put them in two piles at the entrance of the city gate until morning.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The next morning Jehu went out. He stood before all the people and said, “You are innocent. It was I who conspired against my master and killed him, but who killed all these?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Know, then, that not a word the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken against the house of Ahab will fail. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has done what he announced<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9804H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9804H\"></sup> through his servant Elijah.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9804I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9804I\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Jehu<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9805J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9805J\"></sup> killed everyone in Jezreel who remained of the house of Ahab, as well as all his chief men, his close friends and his priests, leaving him no survivor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9805K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9805K\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jehu then set out and went toward Samaria. At Beth Eked of the Shepherds,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>he met some relatives of Ahaziah king of Judah and asked, “Who are you?”They said, “We are relatives of Ahaziah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9807L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9807L\"></sup> and we have come down to greet the families of the king and of the queen mother.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9807M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9807M\"></sup>”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Take them alive!” he ordered. So they took them alive and slaughtered them by the well of Beth Eked—forty-two of them. He left no survivor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9808N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9808N\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>After he left there, he came upon Jehonadab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9809O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9809O\"></sup> son of Rekab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9809P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9809P\"></sup> who was on his way to meet him. Jehu greeted him and said, “Are you in accord with me, as I am with you?”“I am,” Jehonadab answered.“If so,” said Jehu, “give me your hand.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9809Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9809Q\"></sup> So he did, and Jehu helped him up into the chariot.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Jehu said, “Come with me and see my zeal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9810R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9810R\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” Then he had him ride along in his chariot.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Jehu came to Samaria, he killed all who were left there of Ahab’s family;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9811S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9811S\"></sup> he destroyed them, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken to Elijah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Jehu brought all the people together and said to them, “Ahab served<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9812T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9812T\"></sup> Baal a little; Jehu will serve him much.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now summon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9813U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9813U\"></sup> all the prophets of Baal, all his servants and all his priests. See that no one is missing, because I am going to hold a great sacrifice for Baal. Anyone who fails to come will no longer live.” But Jehu was acting deceptively in order to destroy the servants of Baal.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Jehu said, “Call an assembly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9814V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9814V\"></sup> in honor of Baal.” So they proclaimed it.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then he sent word throughout Israel, and all the servants of Baal came; not one stayed away. They crowded into the temple of Baal until it was full from one end to the other.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Jehu said to the keeper of the wardrobe, “Bring robes for all the servants of Baal.” So he brought out robes for them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Jehu and Jehonadab son of Rekab went into the temple of Baal. Jehu said to the servants of Baal, “Look around and see that no one who serves the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is here with you—only servants of Baal.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So they went in to make sacrifices and burnt offerings. Now Jehu had posted eighty men outside with this warning: “If one of you lets any of the men I am placing in your hands escape, it will be your life for his life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9818W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9818W\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As soon as Jehu had finished making the burnt offering, he ordered the guards and officers: “Go in and kill<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9819X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9819X\"></sup> them; let no one escape.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9819Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9819Y\"></sup> So they cut them down with the sword. The guards and officers threw the bodies out and then entered the inner shrine of the temple of Baal.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They brought the sacred stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9820Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9820Z\"></sup> out of the temple of Baal and burned it.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They demolished the sacred stone of Baal and tore down the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9821AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9821AA\"></sup> of Baal, and people have used it for a latrine to this day.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Jehu<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9822AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9822AB\"></sup> destroyed Baal worship in Israel.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>However, he did not turn away from the sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9823AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9823AC\"></sup> of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit—the worship of the golden calves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9823AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9823AD\"></sup> at Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9823AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9823AE\"></sup> and Dan.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Jehu, “Because you have done well in accomplishing what is right in my eyes and have done to the house of Ahab all I had in mind to do, your descendants will sit on the throne of Israel to the fourth generation.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9824AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9824AF\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Yet Jehu was not careful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9825AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9825AG\"></sup> to keep the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, with all his heart. He did not turn away from the sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9825AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9825AH\"></sup> of Jeroboam, which he had caused Israel to commit.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>In those days the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began to reduce<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9826AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9826AI\"></sup> the size of Israel. Hazael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9826AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9826AJ\"></sup> overpowered the Israelites throughout their territory",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>east of the Jordan in all the land of Gilead (the region of Gad, Reuben and Manasseh), from Aroer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9827AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9827AK\"></sup> by the Arnon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9827AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9827AL\"></sup> Gorge through Gilead to Bashan.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>As for the other events of Jehu’s reign, all he did, and all his achievements, are they not written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9828AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9828AM\"></sup> of the kings of Israel?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Jehu rested with his ancestors and was buried in Samaria. And Jehoahaz his son succeeded him as king.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The time that Jehu reigned over Israel in Samaria was twenty-eight years."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>When Athaliah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9831B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9831B\"></sup> the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she proceeded to destroy the whole royal family.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Jehosheba, the daughter of King Jehoram and sister of Ahaziah, took Joash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9832C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9832C\"></sup> son of Ahaziah and stole him away from among the royal princes, who were about to be murdered. She put him and his nurse in a bedroom to hide him from Athaliah; so he was not killed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9832D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9832D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He remained hidden with his nurse at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for six years while Athaliah ruled the land.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>In the seventh year Jehoiada sent for the commanders of units of a hundred, the Carites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9834E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9834E\"></sup> and the guards and had them brought to him at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He made a covenant with them and put them under oath at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then he showed them the king’s son.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He commanded them, saying, “This is what you are to do: You who are in the three companies that are going on duty on the Sabbath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9835F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9835F\"></sup>—a third of you guarding the royal palace,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9835G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9835G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>a third at the Sur Gate, and a third at the gate behind the guard, who take turns guarding the temple—",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and you who are in the other two companies that normally go off Sabbath duty are all to guard the temple for the king.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Station yourselves around the king, each of you with weapon in hand. Anyone who approaches your ranks is to be put to death. Stay close to the king wherever he goes.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The commanders of units of a hundred did just as Jehoiada the priest ordered. Each one took his men—those who were going on duty on the Sabbath and those who were going off duty—and came to Jehoiada the priest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he gave the commanders the spears and shields<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9840H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9840H\"></sup> that had belonged to King David and that were in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The guards, each with weapon in hand, stationed themselves around the king—near the altar and the temple, from the south side to the north side of the temple.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jehoiada brought out the king’s son and put the crown on him; he presented him with a copy of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9842I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9842I\"></sup> and proclaimed him king. They anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9842J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9842J\"></sup> him, and the people clapped their hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9842K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9842K\"></sup> and shouted, “Long live the king!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9842L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9842L\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Athaliah heard the noise made by the guards and the people, she went to the people at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>She looked and there was the king, standing by the pillar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9844M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9844M\"></sup> as the custom was. The officers and the trumpeters were beside the king, and all the people of the land were rejoicing and blowing trumpets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9844N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9844N\"></sup> Then Athaliah tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9844O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9844O\"></sup> her robes and called out, “Treason! Treason!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9844P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9844P\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Jehoiada the priest ordered the commanders of units of a hundred, who were in charge of the troops: “Bring her out between the ranks and put to the sword anyone who follows her.” For the priest had said, “She must not be put to death in the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9845Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9845Q\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they seized her as she reached the place where the horses enter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9846R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9846R\"></sup> the palace grounds, and there she was put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9846S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9846S\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jehoiada then made a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9847T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9847T\"></sup> between the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king and people that they would be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s people. He also made a covenant between the king and the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9847U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9847U\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>All the people of the land went to the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9848V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9848V\"></sup> of Baal and tore it down. They smashed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9848W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9848W\"></sup> the altars and idols to pieces and killed Mattan the priest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9848X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9848X\"></sup> of Baal in front of the altars.Then Jehoiada the priest posted guards at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He took with him the commanders of hundreds, the Carites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9849Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9849Y\"></sup> the guards and all the people of the land, and together they brought the king down from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and went into the palace, entering by way of the gate of the guards. The king then took his place on the royal throne.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All the people of the land rejoiced,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9850Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9850Z\"></sup> and the city was calm, because Athaliah had been slain with the sword at the palace.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Joash was seven years old when he began to reign."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>In the seventh year of Jehu, Joash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9852B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9852B\"></sup> became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem forty years. His mother’s name was Zibiah; she was from Beersheba.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Joash did what was right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9853C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9853C\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the years Jehoiada the priest instructed him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The high places,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9854D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9854D\"></sup> however, were not removed; the people continued to offer sacrifices and burn incense there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Joash said to the priests, “Collect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9855E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9855E\"></sup> all the money that is brought as sacred offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9855F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9855F\"></sup> to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—the money collected in the census,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9855G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9855G\"></sup> the money received from personal vows and the money brought voluntarily<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9855H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9855H\"></sup> to the temple.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let every priest receive the money from one of the treasurers, then use it to repair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9856I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9856I\"></sup> whatever damage is found in the temple.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But by the twenty-third year of King Joash the priests still had not repaired the temple.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore King Joash summoned Jehoiada the priest and the other priests and asked them, “Why aren’t you repairing the damage done to the temple? Take no more money from your treasurers, but hand it over for repairing the temple.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The priests agreed that they would not collect any more money from the people and that they would not repair the temple themselves.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jehoiada the priest took a chest and bored a hole in its lid. He placed it beside the altar, on the right side as one enters the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The priests who guarded the entrance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9860J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9860J\"></sup> put into the chest all the money<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9860K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9860K\"></sup> that was brought to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Whenever they saw that there was a large amount of money in the chest, the royal secretary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9861L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9861L\"></sup> and the high priest came, counted the money that had been brought into the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and put it into bags.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the amount had been determined, they gave the money to the men appointed to supervise the work on the temple. With it they paid those who worked on the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—the carpenters and builders,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the masons and stonecutters.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9863M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9863M\"></sup> They purchased timber and blocks of dressed stone for the repair of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and met all the other expenses of restoring the temple.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The money brought into the temple was not spent for making silver basins, wick trimmers, sprinkling bowls, trumpets or any other articles of gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9864N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9864N\"></sup> or silver for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>it was paid to the workers, who used it to repair the temple.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They did not require an accounting from those to whom they gave the money to pay the workers, because they acted with complete honesty.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9866O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9866O\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The money from the guilt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9867P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9867P\"></sup> and sin offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9867Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9867Q\"></sup> was not brought into the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it belonged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9867R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9867R\"></sup> to the priests.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>About this time Hazael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9868S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9868S\"></sup> king of Aram went up and attacked Gath and captured it. Then he turned to attack Jerusalem.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But Joash king of Judah took all the sacred objects dedicated by his predecessors—Jehoshaphat, Jehoram and Ahaziah, the kings of Judah—and the gifts he himself had dedicated and all the gold found in the treasuries of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and of the royal palace, and he sent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9869T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9869T\"></sup> them to Hazael king of Aram, who then withdrew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9869U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9869U\"></sup> from Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>As for the other events of the reign of Joash, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>His officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9871V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9871V\"></sup> conspired against him and assassinated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9871W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9871W\"></sup> him at Beth Millo,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9871X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9871X\"></sup> on the road down to Silla.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The officials who murdered him were Jozabad son of Shimeath and Jehozabad son of Shomer. He died and was buried with his ancestors in the City of David. And Amaziah his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>In the twenty-third year of Joash son of Ahaziah king of Judah, Jehoahaz son of Jehu became king of Israel in Samaria, and he reigned seventeen years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9874A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9874A\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by following the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit, and he did not turn away from them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9875B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9875B\"></sup> burned against Israel, and for a long time he kept them under the power<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9875C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9875C\"></sup> of Hazael king of Aram and Ben-Hadad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9875D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9875D\"></sup> his son.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Jehoahaz sought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9876E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9876E\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s favor, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> listened to him, for he saw<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9876F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9876F\"></sup> how severely the king of Aram was oppressing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9876G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9876G\"></sup> Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> provided a deliverer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9877H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9877H\"></sup> for Israel, and they escaped from the power of Aram. So the Israelites lived in their own homes as they had before.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But they did not turn away from the sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9878I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9878I\"></sup> of the house of Jeroboam, which he had caused Israel to commit; they continued in them. Also, the Asherah pole<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9878J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9878J\"></sup> remained standing in Samaria.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nothing had been left<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9879K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9879K\"></sup> of the army of Jehoahaz except fifty horsemen, ten chariots and ten thousand foot soldiers, for the king of Aram had destroyed the rest and made them like the dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9879L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9879L\"></sup> at threshing time.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>As for the other events of the reign of Jehoahaz, all he did and his achievements, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jehoahaz rested with his ancestors and was buried in Samaria. And Jehoash his son succeeded him as king.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the thirty-seventh year of Joash king of Judah, Jehoash son of Jehoahaz became king of Israel in Samaria, and he reigned sixteen years.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did not turn away from any of the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit; he continued in them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As for the other events of the reign of Jehoash, all he did and his achievements, including his war against Amaziah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9884M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9884M\"></sup> king of Judah, are they not written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9884N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9884N\"></sup> of the kings of Israel?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jehoash rested with his ancestors, and Jeroboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9885O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9885O\"></sup> succeeded him on the throne. Jehoash was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now Elisha had been suffering from the illness from which he died. Jehoash king of Israel went down to see him and wept over him. “My father! My father!” he cried. “The chariots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9886P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9886P\"></sup> and horsemen of Israel!”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Elisha said, “Get a bow and some arrows,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9887Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9887Q\"></sup> and he did so.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Take the bow in your hands,” he said to the king of Israel. When he had taken it, Elisha put his hands on the king’s hands.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Open the east window,” he said, and he opened it. “Shoot!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9889R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9889R\"></sup> Elisha said, and he shot. “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s arrow of victory, the arrow of victory over Aram!” Elisha declared. “You will completely destroy the Arameans at Aphek.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9889S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9889S\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he said, “Take the arrows,” and the king took them. Elisha told him, “Strike the ground.” He struck it three times and stopped.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The man of God was angry with him and said, “You should have struck the ground five or six times; then you would have defeated Aram and completely destroyed it. But now you will defeat it only three times.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9891T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9891T\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Elisha died and was buried.Now Moabite raiders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9892U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9892U\"></sup> used to enter the country every spring.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Once while some Israelites were burying a man, suddenly they saw a band of raiders; so they threw the man’s body into Elisha’s tomb. When the body touched Elisha’s bones, the man came to life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9893V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9893V\"></sup> and stood up on his feet.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Hazael king of Aram oppressed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9894W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9894W\"></sup> Israel throughout the reign of Jehoahaz.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was gracious to them and had compassion and showed concern for them because of his covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9895X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9895X\"></sup> with Abraham, Isaac and Jacob. To this day he has been unwilling to destroy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9895Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9895Y\"></sup> them or banish them from his presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9895Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9895Z\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hazael king of Aram died, and Ben-Hadad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9896AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9896AA\"></sup> his son succeeded him as king.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Jehoash son of Jehoahaz recaptured from Ben-Hadad son of Hazael the towns he had taken in battle from his father Jehoahaz. Three times<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9897AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9897AB\"></sup> Jehoash defeated him, and so he recovered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9897AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9897AC\"></sup> the Israelite towns."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>In the second year of Jehoash son of Jehoahaz king of Israel, Amaziah son of Joash king of Judah began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem twenty-nine years. His mother’s name was Jehoaddan; she was from Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but not as his father David had done. In everything he followed the example of his father Joash.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The high places,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9901C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9901C\"></sup> however, were not removed; the people continued to offer sacrifices and burn incense there.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>After the kingdom was firmly in his grasp, he executed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9902D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9902D\"></sup> the officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9902E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9902E\"></sup> who had murdered his father the king.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Yet he did not put the children of the assassins to death, in accordance with what is written in the Book of the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9903F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9903F\"></sup> of Moses where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded: “Parents are not to be put to death for their children, nor children put to death for their parents; each will die for their own sin.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9903G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9903G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He was the one who defeated ten thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9904H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9904H\"></sup> and captured Sela<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9904I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9904I\"></sup> in battle, calling it Joktheel, the name it has to this day.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Amaziah sent messengers to Jehoash son of Jehoahaz, the son of Jehu, king of Israel, with the challenge: “Come, let us face each other in battle.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Jehoash king of Israel replied to Amaziah king of Judah: “A thistle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9906J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9906J\"></sup> in Lebanon sent a message to a cedar in Lebanon, ‘Give your daughter to my son in marriage.’ Then a wild beast in Lebanon came along and trampled the thistle underfoot.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You have indeed defeated Edom and now you are arrogant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9907K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9907K\"></sup> Glory in your victory, but stay at home! Why ask for trouble and cause your own downfall and that of Judah also?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Amaziah, however, would not listen, so Jehoash king of Israel attacked. He and Amaziah king of Judah faced each other at Beth Shemesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9908L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9908L\"></sup> in Judah.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Judah was routed by Israel, and every man fled to his home.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9909M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9909M\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Joash, the son of Ahaziah, at Beth Shemesh. Then Jehoash went to Jerusalem and broke down the wall<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9910N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9910N\"></sup> of Jerusalem from the Ephraim Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9910O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9910O\"></sup> to the Corner Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9910P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9910P\"></sup>—a section about four hundred cubits long.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He took all the gold and silver and all the articles found in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in the treasuries of the royal palace. He also took hostages and returned to Samaria.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As for the other events of the reign of Jehoash, what he did and his achievements, including his war<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9912Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9912Q\"></sup> against Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel?",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Jehoash rested with his ancestors and was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel. And Jeroboam his son succeeded him as king.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Amaziah son of Joash king of Judah lived for fifteen years after the death of Jehoash son of Jehoahaz king of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As for the other events of Amaziah’s reign, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They conspired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9916R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9916R\"></sup> against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to Lachish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9916S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9916S\"></sup> but they sent men after him to Lachish and killed him there.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He was brought back by horse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9917T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9917T\"></sup> and was buried in Jerusalem with his ancestors, in the City of David.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then all the people of Judah took Azariah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9918U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9918U\"></sup> who was sixteen years old, and made him king in place of his father Amaziah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He was the one who rebuilt Elath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9919V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9919V\"></sup> and restored it to Judah after Amaziah rested with his ancestors.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the fifteenth year of Amaziah son of Joash king of Judah, Jeroboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9920W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9920W\"></sup> son of Jehoash king of Israel became king in Samaria, and he reigned forty-one years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did not turn away from any of the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9921X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9921X\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He was the one who restored the boundaries of Israel from Lebo Hamath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9922Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9922Y\"></sup> to the Dead Sea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9922Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9922Z\"></sup> in accordance with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, spoken through his servant Jonah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9922AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9922AA\"></sup> son of Amittai, the prophet from Gath Hepher.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had seen how bitterly everyone in Israel, whether slave or free,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9923AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9923AB\"></sup> was suffering;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9923AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9923AC\"></sup> there was no one to help them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9923AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9923AD\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And since the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had not said he would blot out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9924AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9924AE\"></sup> the name of Israel from under heaven, he saved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9924AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9924AF\"></sup> them by the hand of Jeroboam son of Jehoash.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>As for the other events of Jeroboam’s reign, all he did, and his military achievements, including how he recovered for Israel both Damascus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9925AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9925AG\"></sup> and Hamath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9925AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9925AH\"></sup> which had belonged to Judah, are they not written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9925AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9925AI\"></sup> of the kings of Israel?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jeroboam rested with his ancestors, the kings of Israel. And Zechariah his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>In the twenty-seventh year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Azariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9927B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9927B\"></sup> son of Amaziah king of Judah began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem fifty-two years. His mother’s name was Jekoliah; she was from Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He did what was right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9929C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9929C\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his father Amaziah had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The high places, however, were not removed; the people continued to offer sacrifices and burn incense there.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> afflicted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9931D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9931D\"></sup> the king with leprosy until the day he died, and he lived in a separate house.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9931E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9931E\"></sup> Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9931F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9931F\"></sup> the king’s son had charge of the palace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9931G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9931G\"></sup> and governed the people of the land.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>As for the other events of Azariah’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Azariah rested<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9933H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9933H\"></sup> with his ancestors and was buried near them in the City of David. And Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9933I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9933I\"></sup> his son succeeded him as king.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the thirty-eighth year of Azariah king of Judah, Zechariah son of Jeroboam became king of Israel in Samaria, and he reigned six months.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9935J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9935J\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as his predecessors had done. He did not turn away from the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Shallum son of Jabesh conspired against Zechariah. He attacked him in front of the people, assassinated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9936K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9936K\"></sup> him and succeeded him as king.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The other events of Zechariah’s reign are written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9937L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9937L\"></sup> of the kings of Israel.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken to Jehu was fulfilled:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9938M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9938M\"></sup> “Your descendants will sit on the throne of Israel to the fourth generation.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Shallum son of Jabesh became king in the thirty-ninth year of Uzziah king of Judah, and he reigned in Samaria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9939N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9939N\"></sup> one month.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Menahem son of Gadi went from Tirzah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9940O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9940O\"></sup> up to Samaria. He attacked Shallum son of Jabesh in Samaria, assassinated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9940P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9940P\"></sup> him and succeeded him as king.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The other events of Shallum’s reign, and the conspiracy he led, are written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9941Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9941Q\"></sup> of the kings of Israel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At that time Menahem, starting out from Tirzah, attacked Tiphsah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9942R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9942R\"></sup> and everyone in the city and its vicinity, because they refused to open<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9942S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9942S\"></sup> their gates. He sacked Tiphsah and ripped open all the pregnant women.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In the thirty-ninth year of Azariah king of Judah, Menahem son of Gadi became king of Israel, and he reigned in Samaria ten years.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9944T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9944T\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. During his entire reign he did not turn away from the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Pul<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9945U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9945U\"></sup> king of Assyria invaded the land, and Menahem gave him a thousand talents of silver to gain his support and strengthen his own hold on the kingdom.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Menahem exacted this money from Israel. Every wealthy person had to contribute fifty shekels of silver to be given to the king of Assyria. So the king of Assyria withdrew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9946V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9946V\"></sup> and stayed in the land no longer.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As for the other events of Menahem’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel?",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Menahem rested with his ancestors. And Pekahiah his son succeeded him as king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekahiah son of Menahem became king of Israel in Samaria, and he reigned two years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Pekahiah did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9950W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9950W\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He did not turn away from the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>One of his chief officers, Pekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9951X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9951X\"></sup> son of Remaliah, conspired against him. Taking fifty men of Gilead with him, he assassinated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9951Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9951Y\"></sup> Pekahiah, along with Argob and Arieh, in the citadel of the royal palace at Samaria. So Pekah killed Pekahiah and succeeded him as king.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The other events of Pekahiah’s reign, and all he did, are written in the book of the annals of the kings of Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>In the fifty-second year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9953Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9953Z\"></sup> son of Remaliah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9953AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9953AA\"></sup> became king of Israel in Samaria, and he reigned twenty years.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He did not turn away from the sins of Jeroboam son of Nebat, which he had caused Israel to commit.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>In the time of Pekah king of Israel, Tiglath-Pileser<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9955AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9955AB\"></sup> king of Assyria came and took Ijon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9955AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9955AC\"></sup> Abel Beth Maakah, Janoah, Kedesh and Hazor. He took Gilead and Galilee, including all the land of Naphtali,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9955AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9955AD\"></sup> and deported<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9955AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9955AE\"></sup> the people to Assyria.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Hoshea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9956AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9956AF\"></sup> son of Elah conspired against Pekah son of Remaliah. He attacked and assassinated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9956AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9956AG\"></sup> him, and then succeeded him as king in the twentieth year of Jotham son of Uzziah.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As for the other events of Pekah’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9957AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9957AH\"></sup> of the kings of Israel?",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>In the second year of Pekah son of Remaliah king of Israel, Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9958AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9958AJ\"></sup> son of Uzziah king of Judah began to reign.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem sixteen years. His mother’s name was Jerusha daughter of Zadok.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He did what was right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9960AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9960AK\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his father Uzziah had done.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The high places,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9961AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9961AL\"></sup> however, were not removed; the people continued to offer sacrifices and burn incense there. Jotham rebuilt the Upper Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9961AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9961AM\"></sup> of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>As for the other events of Jotham’s reign, and what he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>(In those days the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began to send Rezin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9963AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9963AN\"></sup> king of Aram and Pekah son of Remaliah against Judah.)",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Jotham rested with his ancestors and was buried with them in the City of David, the city of his father. And Ahaz his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>In the seventeenth year of Pekah son of Remaliah, Ahaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9965B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9965B\"></sup> son of Jotham king of Judah began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Ahaz was twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem sixteen years. Unlike David his father, he did not do what was right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9966C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9966C\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He followed the ways of the kings of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9967D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9967D\"></sup> and even sacrificed his son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9967E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9967E\"></sup> in the fire, engaging in the detestable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9967F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9967F\"></sup> practices of the nations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before the Israelites.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He offered sacrifices and burned incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9968G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9968G\"></sup> at the high places, on the hilltops and under every spreading tree.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9968H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9968H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Rezin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9969I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9969I\"></sup> king of Aram and Pekah son of Remaliah king of Israel marched up to fight against Jerusalem and besieged Ahaz, but they could not overpower him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>At that time, Rezin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9970J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9970J\"></sup> king of Aram recovered Elath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9970K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9970K\"></sup> for Aram by driving out the people of Judah. Edomites then moved into Elath and have lived there to this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Ahaz sent messengers to say to Tiglath-Pileser<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9971L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9971L\"></sup> king of Assyria, “I am your servant and vassal. Come up and save<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9971M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9971M\"></sup> me out of the hand of the king of Aram and of the king of Israel, who are attacking me.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Ahaz took the silver and gold found in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in the treasuries of the royal palace and sent it as a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9972N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9972N\"></sup> to the king of Assyria.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The king of Assyria complied by attacking Damascus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9973O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9973O\"></sup> and capturing it. He deported its inhabitants to Kir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9973P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9973P\"></sup> and put Rezin to death.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then King Ahaz went to Damascus to meet Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria. He saw an altar in Damascus and sent to Uriah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9974Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9974Q\"></sup> the priest a sketch of the altar, with detailed plans for its construction.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Uriah the priest built an altar in accordance with all the plans that King Ahaz had sent from Damascus and finished it before King Ahaz returned.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the king came back from Damascus and saw the altar, he approached it and presented offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9976R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9976R\"></sup> on it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He offered up his burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9977S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9977S\"></sup> and grain offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9977T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9977T\"></sup> poured out his drink offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9977U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9977U\"></sup> and splashed the blood of his fellowship offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9977V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9977V\"></sup> against the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>As for the bronze altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9978W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9978W\"></sup> that stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he brought it from the front of the temple—from between the new altar and the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—and put it on the north side of the new altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>King Ahaz then gave these orders to Uriah the priest: “On the large new altar, offer the morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9979X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9979X\"></sup> burnt offering and the evening grain offering, the king’s burnt offering and his grain offering, and the burnt offering of all the people of the land, and their grain offering and their drink offering. Splash against this altar the blood of all the burnt offerings and sacrifices. But I will use the bronze altar for seeking guidance.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9979Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9979Y\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Uriah the priest did just as King Ahaz had ordered.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>King Ahaz cut off the side panels and removed the basins from the movable stands. He removed the Sea from the bronze bulls that supported it and set it on a stone base.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9981Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9981Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He took away the Sabbath canopy that had been built at the temple and removed the royal entryway outside the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in deference to the king of Assyria.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9982AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9982AA\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>As for the other events of the reign of Ahaz, and what he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Ahaz rested<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9984AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9984AB\"></sup> with his ancestors and was buried with them in the City of David. And Hezekiah his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>In the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah, Hoshea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9985B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9985B\"></sup> son of Elah became king of Israel in Samaria, and he reigned nine years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9986C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9986C\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but not like the kings of Israel who preceded him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Shalmaneser<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9987D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9987D\"></sup> king of Assyria came up to attack Hoshea, who had been Shalmaneser’s vassal and had paid him tribute.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9987E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9987E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the king of Assyria discovered that Hoshea was a traitor, for he had sent envoys to So king of Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9988F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9988F\"></sup> and he no longer paid tribute to the king of Assyria, as he had done year by year. Therefore Shalmaneser seized him and put him in prison.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9988G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9988G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king of Assyria invaded the entire land, marched against Samaria and laid siege<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9989H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9989H\"></sup> to it for three years.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In the ninth year of Hoshea, the king of Assyria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9990I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9990I\"></sup> captured Samaria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9990J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9990J\"></sup> and deported<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9990K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9990K\"></sup> the Israelites to Assyria. He settled them in Halah, in Gozan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9990L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9990L\"></sup> on the Habor River and in the towns of the Medes.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>All this took place because the Israelites had sinned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9991M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9991M\"></sup> against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, who had brought them up out of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9991N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9991N\"></sup> from under the power of Pharaoh king of Egypt. They worshiped other gods",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and followed the practices of the nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9992O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9992O\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before them, as well as the practices that the kings of Israel had introduced.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The Israelites secretly did things against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God that were not right. From watchtower to fortified city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9993P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9993P\"></sup> they built themselves high places in all their towns.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They set up sacred stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9994Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9994Q\"></sup> and Asherah poles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9994R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9994R\"></sup> on every high hill and under every spreading tree.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9994S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9994S\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>At every high place they burned incense, as the nations whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before them had done. They did wicked things that aroused the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They worshiped idols,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9996T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9996T\"></sup> though the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said, “You shall not do this.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> warned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9997U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9997U\"></sup> Israel and Judah through all his prophets and seers:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9997V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9997V\"></sup> “Turn from your evil ways.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9997W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9997W\"></sup> Observe my commands and decrees, in accordance with the entire Law that I commanded your ancestors to obey and that I delivered to you through my servants the prophets.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9997X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9997X\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But they would not listen and were as stiff-necked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9998Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9998Y\"></sup> as their ancestors, who did not trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They rejected his decrees and the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9999Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9999Z\"></sup> he had made with their ancestors and the statutes he had warned them to keep. They followed worthless idols<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9999AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9999AA\"></sup> and themselves became worthless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9999AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9999AB\"></sup> They imitated the nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9999AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9999AC\"></sup> around them although the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had ordered them, “Do not do as they do.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They forsook all the commands of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God and made for themselves two idols cast in the shape of calves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10000AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10000AD\"></sup> and an Asherah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10000AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10000AE\"></sup> pole. They bowed down to all the starry hosts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10000AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10000AF\"></sup> and they worshiped Baal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10000AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10000AG\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They sacrificed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10001AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10001AH\"></sup> their sons and daughters in the fire. They practiced divination and sought omens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10001AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10001AI\"></sup> and sold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10001AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10001AJ\"></sup> themselves to do evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, arousing his anger.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was very angry with Israel and removed them from his presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10002AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10002AK\"></sup> Only the tribe of Judah was left,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and even Judah did not keep the commands of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God. They followed the practices Israel had introduced.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10003AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10003AL\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rejected all the people of Israel; he afflicted them and gave them into the hands of plunderers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10004AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10004AM\"></sup> until he thrust them from his presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10004AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10004AN\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When he tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10005AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10005AO\"></sup> Israel away from the house of David, they made Jeroboam son of Nebat their king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10005AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10005AP\"></sup> Jeroboam enticed Israel away from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and caused them to commit a great sin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10005AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10005AQ\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The Israelites persisted in all the sins of Jeroboam and did not turn away from them",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> removed them from his presence,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10007AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10007AR\"></sup> as he had warned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10007AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10007AS\"></sup> through all his servants the prophets. So the people of Israel were taken from their homeland<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10007AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10007AT\"></sup> into exile in Assyria, and they are still there.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The king of Assyria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10008AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10008AU\"></sup> brought people from Babylon, Kuthah, Avva, Hamath and Sepharvaim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10008AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10008AV\"></sup> and settled them in the towns of Samaria to replace the Israelites. They took over Samaria and lived in its towns.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When they first lived there, they did not worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; so he sent lions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10009AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10009AW\"></sup> among them and they killed some of the people.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>It was reported to the king of Assyria: “The people you deported and resettled in the towns of Samaria do not know what the god of that country requires. He has sent lions among them, which are killing them off, because the people do not know what he requires.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the king of Assyria gave this order: “Have one of the priests you took captive from Samaria go back to live there and teach the people what the god of the land requires.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So one of the priests who had been exiled from Samaria came to live in Bethel and taught them how to worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Nevertheless, each national group made its own gods in the several towns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10013AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10013AX\"></sup> where they settled, and set them up in the shrines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10013AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10013AY\"></sup> the people of Samaria had made at the high places.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10013AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10013AZ\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The people from Babylon made Sukkoth Benoth, those from Kuthah made Nergal, and those from Hamath made Ashima;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>the Avvites made Nibhaz and Tartak, and the Sepharvites burned their children in the fire as sacrifices to Adrammelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10015BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10015BA\"></sup> and Anammelek, the gods of Sepharvaim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10015BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10015BB\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but they also appointed all sorts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10016BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10016BC\"></sup> of their own people to officiate for them as priests in the shrines at the high places.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but they also served their own gods in accordance with the customs of the nations from which they had been brought.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>To this day they persist in their former practices. They neither worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> nor adhere to the decrees and regulations, the laws and commands that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave the descendants of Jacob, whom he named Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10018BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10018BD\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with the Israelites, he commanded them: “Do not worship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10019BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10019BE\"></sup> any other gods or bow down to them, serve them or sacrifice to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10019BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10019BF\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who brought you up out of Egypt with mighty power and outstretched arm,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10020BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10020BG\"></sup> is the one you must worship. To him you shall bow down and to him offer sacrifices.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You must always be careful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10021BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10021BH\"></sup> to keep the decrees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10021BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10021BI\"></sup> and regulations, the laws and commands he wrote for you. Do not worship other gods.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Do not forget<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10022BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10022BJ\"></sup> the covenant I have made with you, and do not worship other gods.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Rather, worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; it is he who will deliver you from the hand of all your enemies.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They would not listen, however, but persisted in their former practices.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Even while these people were worshiping the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10025BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10025BK\"></sup> they were serving their idols. To this day their children and grandchildren continue to do as their ancestors did."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>In the third year of Hoshea son of Elah king of Israel, Hezekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10026D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10026D\"></sup> son of Ahaz king of Judah began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem twenty-nine years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10027E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10027E\"></sup> His mother’s name was Abijah daughter of Zechariah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He did what was right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10028F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10028F\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his father David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10028G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10028G\"></sup> had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He removed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10029H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10029H\"></sup> the high places,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10029I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10029I\"></sup> smashed the sacred stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10029J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10029J\"></sup> and cut down the Asherah poles. He broke into pieces the bronze snake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10029K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10029K\"></sup> Moses had made, for up to that time the Israelites had been burning incense to it. (It was called Nehushtan.)",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Hezekiah trusted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10030L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10030L\"></sup> in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel. There was no one like him among all the kings of Judah, either before him or after him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He held fast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10031M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10031M\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did not stop following him; he kept the commands the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given Moses.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him; he was successful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10032N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10032N\"></sup> in whatever he undertook. He rebelled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10032O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10032O\"></sup> against the king of Assyria and did not serve him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From watchtower to fortified city,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10033P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10033P\"></sup> he defeated the Philistines, as far as Gaza and its territory.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>In King Hezekiah’s fourth year,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10034Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10034Q\"></sup> which was the seventh year of Hoshea son of Elah king of Israel, Shalmaneser king of Assyria marched against Samaria and laid siege to it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At the end of three years the Assyrians took it. So Samaria was captured in Hezekiah’s sixth year, which was the ninth year of Hoshea king of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10036R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10036R\"></sup> of Assyria deported Israel to Assyria and settled them in Halah, in Gozan on the Habor River and in towns of the Medes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10036S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10036S\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>This happened because they had not obeyed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, but had violated his covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10037T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10037T\"></sup>—all that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10037U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10037U\"></sup> They neither listened to the commands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10037V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10037V\"></sup> nor carried them out.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>In the fourteenth year<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10038W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10038W\"></sup> of King Hezekiah’s reign, Sennacherib king of Assyria attacked all the fortified cities of Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10038X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10038X\"></sup> and captured them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Hezekiah king of Judah sent this message to the king of Assyria at Lachish:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10039Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10039Y\"></sup> “I have done wrong.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10039Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10039Z\"></sup> Withdraw from me, and I will pay whatever you demand of me.” The king of Assyria exacted from Hezekiah king of Judah three hundred talents of silver and thirty talents of gold.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Hezekiah gave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10040AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10040AA\"></sup> him all the silver that was found in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in the treasuries of the royal palace.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At this time Hezekiah king of Judah stripped off the gold with which he had covered the doors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10041AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10041AB\"></sup> and doorposts of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and gave it to the king of Assyria.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The king of Assyria sent his supreme commander,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10042AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10042AE\"></sup> his chief officer and his field commander with a large army, from Lachish to King Hezekiah at Jerusalem. They came up to Jerusalem and stopped at the aqueduct of the Upper Pool,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10042AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10042AF\"></sup> on the road to the Washerman’s Field.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They called for the king; and Eliakim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10043AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10043AG\"></sup> son of Hilkiah the palace administrator, Shebna<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10043AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10043AH\"></sup> the secretary, and Joah son of Asaph the recorder went out to them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The field commander said to them, “Tell Hezekiah:“‘This is what the great king, the king of Assyria, says: On what are you basing this confidence<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10044AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10044AI\"></sup> of yours?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You say you have the counsel and the might for war—but you speak only empty words. On whom are you depending, that you rebel against me?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Look, I know you are depending on Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10046AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10046AJ\"></sup> that splintered reed of a staff,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10046AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10046AK\"></sup> which pierces the hand of anyone who leans on it! Such is Pharaoh king of Egypt to all who depend on him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But if you say to me, “We are depending on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God”—isn’t he the one whose high places and altars Hezekiah removed, saying to Judah and Jerusalem, “You must worship before this altar in Jerusalem”?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“‘Come now, make a bargain with my master, the king of Assyria: I will give you two thousand horses—if you can put riders on them!",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>How can you repulse one officer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10049AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10049AL\"></sup> of the least of my master’s officials, even though you are depending on Egypt for chariots and horsemen?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Furthermore, have I come to attack and destroy this place without word from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10050AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10050AM\"></sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself told me to march against this country and destroy it.’”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Eliakim son of Hilkiah, and Shebna and Joah said to the field commander, “Please speak to your servants in Aramaic,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10051AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10051AN\"></sup> since we understand it. Don’t speak to us in Hebrew in the hearing of the people on the wall.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But the commander replied, “Was it only to your master and you that my master sent me to say these things, and not to the people sitting on the wall—who, like you, will have to eat their own excrement and drink their own urine?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the commander stood and called out in Hebrew, “Hear the word of the great king, the king of Assyria!",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>This is what the king says: Do not let Hezekiah deceive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10054AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10054AO\"></sup> you. He cannot deliver you from my hand.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Do not let Hezekiah persuade you to trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> when he says, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will surely deliver us; this city will not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.’",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Do not listen to Hezekiah. This is what the king of Assyria says: Make peace with me and come out to me. Then each of you will eat fruit from your own vine and fig tree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10056AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10056AP\"></sup> and drink water from your own cistern,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10056AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10056AQ\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>until I come and take you to a land like your own—a land of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards, a land of olive trees and honey. Choose life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10057AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10057AR\"></sup> and not death!“Do not listen to Hezekiah, for he is misleading you when he says, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will deliver us.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Has the god<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10058AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10058AS\"></sup> of any nation ever delivered his land from the hand of the king of Assyria?",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Where are the gods of Hamath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10059AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10059AT\"></sup> and Arpad?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10059AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10059AU\"></sup> Where are the gods of Sepharvaim, Hena and Ivvah? Have they rescued Samaria from my hand?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Who of all the gods of these countries has been able to save his land from me? How then can the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> deliver Jerusalem from my hand?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10060AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10060AV\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But the people remained silent and said nothing in reply, because the king had commanded, “Do not answer him.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then Eliakim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10062AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10062AW\"></sup> son of Hilkiah the palace administrator, Shebna the secretary, and Joah son of Asaph the recorder went to Hezekiah, with their clothes torn,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10062AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10062AX\"></sup> and told him what the field commander had said."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>When King Hezekiah heard this, he tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10063B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10063B\"></sup> his clothes and put on sackcloth and went into the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He sent Eliakim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10064C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10064C\"></sup> the palace administrator, Shebna the secretary and the leading priests,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10064D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10064D\"></sup> all wearing sackcloth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10064E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10064E\"></sup> to the prophet Isaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10064F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10064F\"></sup> son of Amoz.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They told him, “This is what Hezekiah says: This day is a day of distress and rebuke and disgrace, as when children come to the moment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10065G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10065G\"></sup> of birth and there is no strength to deliver them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>It may be that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will hear all the words of the field commander, whom his master, the king of Assyria, has sent to ridicule<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10066H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10066H\"></sup> the living God, and that he will rebuke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10066I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10066I\"></sup> him for the words the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has heard. Therefore pray for the remnant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10066J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10066J\"></sup> that still survives.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When King Hezekiah’s officials came to Isaiah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Isaiah said to them, “Tell your master, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: Do not be afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10068K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10068K\"></sup> of what you have heard—those words with which the underlings of the king of Assyria have blasphemed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10068L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10068L\"></sup> me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Listen! When he hears a certain report,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10069M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10069M\"></sup> I will make him want to return to his own country, and there I will have him cut down with the sword.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10069N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10069N\"></sup>’”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the field commander heard that the king of Assyria had left Lachish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10070O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10070O\"></sup> he withdrew and found the king fighting against Libnah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10070P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10070P\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now Sennacherib received a report that Tirhakah, the king of Cush, was marching out to fight against him. So he again sent messengers to Hezekiah with this word:",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Say to Hezekiah king of Judah: Do not let the god you depend<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10072Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10072Q\"></sup> on deceive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10072R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10072R\"></sup> you when he says, ‘Jerusalem will not be given into the hands of the king of Assyria.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Surely you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all the countries, destroying them completely. And will you be delivered?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Did the gods of the nations that were destroyed by my predecessors deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10074S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10074S\"></sup> them—the gods of Gozan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10074T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10074T\"></sup> Harran,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10074U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10074U\"></sup> Rezeph and the people of Eden who were in Tel Assar?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Where is the king of Hamath or the king of Arpad? Where are the kings of Lair, Sepharvaim, Hena and Ivvah?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10075V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10075V\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Hezekiah received the letter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10076X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10076X\"></sup> from the messengers and read it. Then he went up to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and spread it out before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Hezekiah prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, enthroned between the cherubim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10077Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10077Y\"></sup> you alone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10077Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10077Z\"></sup> are God over all the kingdoms of the earth. You have made heaven and earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Give ear,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10078AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10078AA\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and hear;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10078AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10078AB\"></sup> open your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10078AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10078AC\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and see; listen to the words Sennacherib has sent to ridicule the living God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“It is true, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the Assyrian kings have laid waste these nations and their lands.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They have thrown their gods into the fire and destroyed them, for they were not gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10080AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10080AD\"></sup> but only wood and stone, fashioned by human hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10080AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10080AE\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10081AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10081AF\"></sup> us from his hand, so that all the kingdoms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10081AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10081AG\"></sup> of the earth may know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10081AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10081AH\"></sup> that you alone, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, are God.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Isaiah son of Amoz sent a message to Hezekiah: “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: I have heard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10082AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10082AK\"></sup> your prayer concerning Sennacherib king of Assyria.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>This is the word that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken against<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10083AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10083AL\"></sup> him:“‘Virgin Daughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10083AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10083AM\"></sup> Ziondespises<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10083AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10083AN\"></sup> you and mocks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10083AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10083AO\"></sup> you.Daughter Jerusalemtosses her head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10083AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10083AP\"></sup> as you flee.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Who is it you have ridiculed and blasphemed?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10084AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10084AQ\"></sup>Against whom have you raised your voiceand lifted your eyes in pride?Against the Holy One<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10084AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10084AR\"></sup> of Israel!",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>By your messengersyou have ridiculed the Lord.And you have said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10085AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10085AS\"></sup>“With my many chariots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10085AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10085AT\"></sup>I have ascended the heights of the mountains,the utmost heights of Lebanon.I have cut down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10085AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10085AU\"></sup> its tallest cedars,the choicest of its junipers.I have reached its remotest parts,the finest of its forests.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I have dug wells in foreign landsand drunk the water there.With the soles of my feetI have dried up all the streams of Egypt.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“‘Have you not heard?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10087AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10087AV\"></sup>Long ago I ordained it.In days of old I planned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10087AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10087AW\"></sup> it;now I have brought it to pass,that you have turned fortified citiesinto piles of stone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10087AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10087AX\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Their people, drained of power,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10088AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10088AY\"></sup>are dismayed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10088AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10088AZ\"></sup> and put to shame.They are like plants in the field,like tender green shoots,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10088BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10088BA\"></sup>like grass sprouting on the roof,scorched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10088BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10088BB\"></sup> before it grows up.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“‘But I know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10089BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10089BC\"></sup> where you areand when you come and goand how you rage against me.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Because you rage against meand because your insolence has reached my ears,I will put my hook<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10090BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10090BD\"></sup> in your noseand my bit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10090BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10090BE\"></sup> in your mouth,and I will make you return<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10090BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10090BF\"></sup>by the way you came.’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“This will be the sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10091BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10091BG\"></sup> for you, Hezekiah:“This year you will eat what grows by itself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10091BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10091BH\"></sup>and the second year what springs from that.But in the third year sow and reap,plant vineyards<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10091BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10091BI\"></sup> and eat their fruit.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Once more a remnant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10092BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10092BJ\"></sup> of the kingdom of Judahwill take root<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10092BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10092BK\"></sup> below and bear fruit above.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For out of Jerusalem will come a remnant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10093BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10093BL\"></sup>and out of Mount Zion a band of survivors.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10093BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10093BM\"></sup>“The zeal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10093BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10093BN\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Almighty will accomplish this.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Therefore this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says concerning the king of Assyria:“‘He will not enter this cityor shoot an arrow here.He will not come before it with shieldor build a siege ramp against it.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>By the way that he came he will return;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10095BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10095BO\"></sup>he will not enter this city,declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>I will defend<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10096BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10096BP\"></sup> this city and save it,for my sake and for the sake of David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10096BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10096BQ\"></sup> my servant.’”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>That night the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10097BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10097BR\"></sup> went out and put to death a hundred and eighty-five thousand in the Assyrian camp. When the people got up the next morning—there were all the dead bodies!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10097BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10097BS\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>So Sennacherib king of Assyria broke camp and withdrew.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10098BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10098BT\"></sup> He returned to Nineveh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10098BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10098BU\"></sup> and stayed there.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>One day, while he was worshiping in the temple of his god Nisrok, his sons Adrammelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10099BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10099BV\"></sup> and Sharezer killed him with the sword,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10099BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10099BW\"></sup> and they escaped to the land of Ararat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10099BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10099BX\"></sup> And Esarhaddon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10099BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10099BY\"></sup> his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>In those days Hezekiah became ill and was at the point of death. The prophet Isaiah son of Amoz went to him and said, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: Put your house in order, because you are going to die; you will not recover.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Remember,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10102B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10102B\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, how I have walked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10102C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10102C\"></sup> before you faithfully<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10102D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10102D\"></sup> and with wholehearted devotion and have done what is good in your eyes.” And Hezekiah wept bitterly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Before Isaiah had left the middle court, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him:",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Go back and tell Hezekiah, the ruler of my people, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your father David, says: I have heard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10104E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10104E\"></sup> your prayer and seen your tears;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10104F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10104F\"></sup> I will heal you. On the third day from now you will go up to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I will add fifteen years to your life. And I will deliver you and this city from the hand of the king of Assyria. I will defend<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10105G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10105G\"></sup> this city for my sake and for the sake of my servant David.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Isaiah said, “Prepare a poultice of figs.” They did so and applied it to the boil,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10106H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10106H\"></sup> and he recovered.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Hezekiah had asked Isaiah, “What will be the sign that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will heal me and that I will go up to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the third day from now?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Isaiah answered, “This is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10108I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10108I\"></sup> to you that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do what he has promised: Shall the shadow go forward ten steps, or shall it go back ten steps?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“It is a simple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10109J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10109J\"></sup> matter for the shadow to go forward ten steps,” said Hezekiah. “Rather, have it go back ten steps.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the prophet Isaiah called on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made the shadow go back<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10110K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10110K\"></sup> the ten steps it had gone down on the stairway of Ahaz.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>At that time Marduk-Baladan son of Baladan king of Babylon sent Hezekiah letters and a gift, because he had heard of Hezekiah’s illness.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hezekiah received the envoys and showed them all that was in his storehouses—the silver, the gold, the spices and the fine olive oil—his armory and everything found among his treasures. There was nothing in his palace or in all his kingdom that Hezekiah did not show them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Isaiah the prophet went to King Hezekiah and asked, “What did those men say, and where did they come from?”“From a distant land,” Hezekiah replied. “They came from Babylon.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The prophet asked, “What did they see in your palace?”“They saw everything in my palace,” Hezekiah said. “There is nothing among my treasures that I did not show them.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, “Hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The time will surely come when everything in your palace, and all that your predecessors have stored up until this day, will be carried off to Babylon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10116N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10116N\"></sup> Nothing will be left, says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And some of your descendants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10117O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10117O\"></sup> your own flesh and blood who will be born to you, will be taken away, and they will become eunuchs in the palace of the king of Babylon.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10117P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10117P\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“The word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> you have spoken is good,” Hezekiah replied. For he thought, “Will there not be peace and security in my lifetime?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for the other events of Hezekiah’s reign, all his achievements and how he made the pool<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10119Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10119Q\"></sup> and the tunnel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10119R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10119R\"></sup> by which he brought water into the city, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Hezekiah rested with his ancestors. And Manasseh his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem fifty-five years. His mother’s name was Hephzibah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10121C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10121C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10122D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10122D\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, following the detestable practices<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10122E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10122E\"></sup> of the nations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before the Israelites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He rebuilt the high places<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10123F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10123F\"></sup> his father Hezekiah had destroyed; he also erected altars to Baal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10123G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10123G\"></sup> and made an Asherah pole,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10123H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10123H\"></sup> as Ahab king of Israel had done. He bowed down to all the starry hosts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10123I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10123I\"></sup> and worshiped them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He built altars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10124J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10124J\"></sup> in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said, “In Jerusalem I will put my Name.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10124K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10124K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In the two courts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10125L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10125L\"></sup> of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he built altars to all the starry hosts.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He sacrificed his own son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10126M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10126M\"></sup> in the fire, practiced divination,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10126N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10126N\"></sup> sought omens, and consulted mediums and spiritists.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10126O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10126O\"></sup> He did much evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, arousing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10126P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10126P\"></sup> his anger.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He took the carved Asherah pole<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10127Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10127Q\"></sup> he had made and put it in the temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10127R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10127R\"></sup> of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to David and to his son Solomon, “In this temple and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, I will put my Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10127S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10127S\"></sup> forever.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I will not again<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10128T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10128T\"></sup> make the feet of the Israelites wander from the land I gave their ancestors, if only they will be careful to do everything I commanded them and will keep the whole Law that my servant Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10128U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10128U\"></sup> gave them.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the people did not listen. Manasseh led them astray, so that they did more evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10129V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10129V\"></sup> than the nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10129W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10129W\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had destroyed before the Israelites.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said through his servants the prophets:",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Manasseh king of Judah has committed these detestable sins. He has done more evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10131X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10131X\"></sup> than the Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10131Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10131Y\"></sup> who preceded him and has led Judah into sin with his idols.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10131Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10131Z\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Therefore this is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: I am going to bring such disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10132AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10132AA\"></sup> on Jerusalem and Judah that the ears of everyone who hears of it will tingle.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10132AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10132AB\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I will stretch out over Jerusalem the measuring line used against Samaria and the plumb line<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10133AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10133AC\"></sup> used against the house of Ahab. I will wipe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10133AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10133AD\"></sup> out Jerusalem as one wipes a dish, wiping it and turning it upside down.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I will forsake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10134AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10134AE\"></sup> the remnant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10134AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10134AF\"></sup> of my inheritance and give them into the hands of enemies. They will be looted and plundered by all their enemies;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>they have done evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10135AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10135AG\"></sup> in my eyes and have aroused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10135AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10135AH\"></sup> my anger from the day their ancestors came out of Egypt until this day.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Moreover, Manasseh also shed so much innocent blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10136AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10136AI\"></sup> that he filled Jerusalem from end to end—besides the sin that he had caused Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10136AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10136AJ\"></sup> to commit, so that they did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As for the other events of Manasseh’s reign, and all he did, including the sin he committed, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Manasseh rested with his ancestors and was buried in his palace garden,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10138AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10138AK\"></sup> the garden of Uzza. And Amon his son succeeded him as king.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem two years. His mother’s name was Meshullemeth daughter of Haruz; she was from Jotbah.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10140AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10140AM\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as his father Manasseh had done.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He followed completely the ways of his father, worshiping the idols his father had worshiped, and bowing down to them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He forsook<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10142AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10142AN\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his ancestors, and did not walk<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10142AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10142AO\"></sup> in obedience to him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Amon’s officials conspired against him and assassinated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10143AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10143AP\"></sup> the king in his palace.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the people of the land killed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10144AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10144AQ\"></sup> all who had plotted against King Amon, and they made Josiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10144AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10144AR\"></sup> his son king in his place.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As for the other events of Amon’s reign, and what he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He was buried in his tomb in the garden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10146AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10146AS\"></sup> of Uzza. And Josiah his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Josiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10147B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10147B\"></sup> was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem thirty-one years. His mother’s name was Jedidah daughter of Adaiah; she was from Bozkath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10147C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10147C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did what was right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10148D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10148D\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and followed completely the ways of his father David, not turning aside to the right<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10148E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10148E\"></sup> or to the left.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the eighteenth year of his reign, King Josiah sent the secretary, Shaphan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10149F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10149F\"></sup> son of Azaliah, the son of Meshullam, to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He said:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Go up to Hilkiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10150G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10150G\"></sup> the high priest and have him get ready the money that has been brought into the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which the doorkeepers have collected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10150H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10150H\"></sup> from the people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Have them entrust it to the men appointed to supervise the work on the temple. And have these men pay the workers who repair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10151I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10151I\"></sup> the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>the carpenters, the builders and the masons. Also have them purchase timber and dressed stone to repair the temple.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10152J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10152J\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But they need not account for the money entrusted to them, because they are honest in their dealings.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10153K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10153K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Hilkiah the high priest said to Shaphan the secretary, “I have found the Book of the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10154L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10154L\"></sup> in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” He gave it to Shaphan, who read it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Shaphan the secretary went to the king and reported to him: “Your officials have paid out the money that was in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and have entrusted it to the workers and supervisors at the temple.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Shaphan the secretary informed the king, “Hilkiah the priest has given me a book.” And Shaphan read from it in the presence of the king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10156M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10156M\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the king heard the words of the Book of the Law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10157N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10157N\"></sup> he tore his robes.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He gave these orders to Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10158O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10158O\"></sup> son of Shaphan, Akbor son of Micaiah, Shaphan the secretary and Asaiah the king’s attendant:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10158P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10158P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Go and inquire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10159Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10159Q\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for me and for the people and for all Judah about what is written in this book that has been found. Great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10159R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10159R\"></sup> that burns against us because those who have gone before us have not obeyed the words of this book; they have not acted in accordance with all that is written there concerning us.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam, Akbor, Shaphan and Asaiah went to speak to the prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10160S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10160S\"></sup> Huldah, who was the wife of Shallum son of Tikvah, the son of Harhas, keeper of the wardrobe. She lived in Jerusalem, in the New Quarter.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>She said to them, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: Tell the man who sent you to me,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: I am going to bring disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10162T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10162T\"></sup> on this place and its people, according to everything written in the book<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10162U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10162U\"></sup> the king of Judah has read.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Because they have forsaken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10163V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10163V\"></sup> me and burned incense to other gods and aroused my anger by all the idols their hands have made, my anger will burn against this place and will not be quenched.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Tell the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10164W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10164W\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says concerning the words you heard:",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Because your heart was responsive and you humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10165X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10165X\"></sup> yourself before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> when you heard what I have spoken against this place and its people—that they would become a curse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10165Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10165Y\"></sup> and be laid waste<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10165Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10165Z\"></sup>—and because you tore your robes and wept in my presence, I also have heard you, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Therefore I will gather you to your ancestors, and you will be buried in peace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10166AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10166AA\"></sup> Your eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10166AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10166AB\"></sup> will not see all the disaster I am going to bring on this place.’”So they took her answer back to the king."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Then the king called together all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He went up to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the people of Judah, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the priests and the prophets—all the people from the least to the greatest. He read<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10168E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10168E\"></sup> in their hearing all the words of the Book of the Covenant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10168F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10168F\"></sup> which had been found in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The king stood by the pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10169G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10169G\"></sup> and renewed the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10169H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10169H\"></sup> in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—to follow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10169I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10169I\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and keep his commands, statutes and decrees with all his heart and all his soul, thus confirming the words of the covenant written in this book. Then all the people pledged themselves to the covenant.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king ordered Hilkiah the high priest, the priests next in rank and the doorkeepers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10170J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10170J\"></sup> to remove<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10170K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10170K\"></sup> from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the articles made for Baal and Asherah and all the starry hosts. He burned them outside Jerusalem in the fields of the Kidron Valley and took the ashes to Bethel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He did away with the idolatrous priests appointed by the kings of Judah to burn incense on the high places of the towns of Judah and on those around Jerusalem—those who burned incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10171L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10171L\"></sup> to Baal, to the sun and moon, to the constellations and to all the starry hosts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10171M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10171M\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He took the Asherah pole from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the Kidron Valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10172N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10172N\"></sup> outside Jerusalem and burned it there. He ground it to powder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10172O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10172O\"></sup> and scattered the dust over the graves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10172P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10172P\"></sup> of the common people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10172Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10172Q\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He also tore down the quarters of the male shrine prostitutes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10173R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10173R\"></sup> that were in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the quarters where women did weaving for Asherah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Josiah brought all the priests from the towns of Judah and desecrated the high places, from Geba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10174S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10174S\"></sup> to Beersheba, where the priests had burned incense. He broke down the gateway at the entrance of the Gate of Joshua, the city governor, which was on the left of the city gate.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Although the priests of the high places did not serve<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10175T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10175T\"></sup> at the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem, they ate unleavened bread with their fellow priests.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He desecrated Topheth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10176U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10176U\"></sup> which was in the Valley of Ben Hinnom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10176V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10176V\"></sup> so no one could use it to sacrifice their son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10176W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10176W\"></sup> or daughter in the fire to Molek.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He removed from the entrance to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the horses that the kings of Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10177X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10177X\"></sup> had dedicated to the sun. They were in the court near the room of an official named Nathan-Melek. Josiah then burned the chariots dedicated to the sun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10177Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10177Y\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He pulled down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10178Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10178Z\"></sup> the altars the kings of Judah had erected on the roof<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10178AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10178AA\"></sup> near the upper room of Ahaz, and the altars Manasseh had built in the two courts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10178AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10178AB\"></sup> of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He removed them from there, smashed them to pieces and threw the rubble into the Kidron Valley.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10178AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10178AC\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king also desecrated the high places that were east of Jerusalem on the south of the Hill of Corruption—the ones Solomon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10179AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10179AD\"></sup> king of Israel had built for Ashtoreth the vile goddess of the Sidonians, for Chemosh the vile god of Moab, and for Molek the detestable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10179AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10179AE\"></sup> god of the people of Ammon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10179AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10179AF\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Josiah smashed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10180AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10180AG\"></sup> the sacred stones and cut down the Asherah poles and covered the sites with human bones.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10180AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10180AH\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Even the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10181AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10181AI\"></sup> at Bethel, the high place made by Jeroboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10181AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10181AJ\"></sup> son of Nebat, who had caused Israel to sin—even that altar and high place he demolished. He burned the high place and ground it to powder, and burned the Asherah pole also.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Josiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10182AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10182AK\"></sup> looked around, and when he saw the tombs that were there on the hillside, he had the bones removed from them and burned on the altar to defile it, in accordance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10182AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10182AL\"></sup> with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> proclaimed by the man of God who foretold these things.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The king asked, “What is that tombstone I see?”The people of the city said, “It marks the tomb of the man of God who came from Judah and pronounced against the altar of Bethel the very things you have done to it.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Leave it alone,” he said. “Don’t let anyone disturb his bones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10184AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10184AM\"></sup>.” So they spared his bones and those of the prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10184AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10184AN\"></sup> who had come from Samaria.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Just as he had done at Bethel, Josiah removed all the shrines at the high places that the kings of Israel had built in the towns of Samaria and that had aroused the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Josiah slaughtered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10186AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10186AO\"></sup> all the priests of those high places on the altars and burned human bones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10186AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10186AP\"></sup> on them. Then he went back to Jerusalem.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The king gave this order to all the people: “Celebrate the Passover<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10187AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10187AQ\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, as it is written in this Book of the Covenant.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10187AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10187AR\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Neither in the days of the judges who led Israel nor in the days of the kings of Israel and the kings of Judah had any such Passover been observed.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But in the eighteenth year of King Josiah, this Passover was celebrated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10189AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10189AS\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Furthermore, Josiah got rid of the mediums and spiritists,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10190AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10190AT\"></sup> the household gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10190AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10190AU\"></sup> the idols and all the other detestable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10190AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10190AV\"></sup> things seen in Judah and Jerusalem. This he did to fulfill the requirements of the law written in the book that Hilkiah the priest had discovered in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Neither before nor after Josiah was there a king like him who turned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10191AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10191AW\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as he did—with all his heart and with all his soul and with all his strength, in accordance with all the Law of Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10191AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10191AX\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Nevertheless, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did not turn away from the heat of his fierce anger,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10192AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10192AY\"></sup> which burned against Judah because of all that Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10192AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10192AZ\"></sup> had done to arouse his anger.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I will remove<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10193BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10193BA\"></sup> Judah also from my presence<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10193BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10193BB\"></sup> as I removed Israel, and I will reject<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10193BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10193BC\"></sup> Jerusalem, the city I chose, and this temple, about which I said, ‘My Name shall be there.’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>As for the other events of Josiah’s reign, and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>While Josiah was king, Pharaoh Necho<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10195BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10195BD\"></sup> king of Egypt went up to the Euphrates River to help the king of Assyria. King Josiah marched out to meet him in battle, but Necho faced him and killed him at Megiddo.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10195BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10195BE\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Josiah’s servants brought his body in a chariot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10196BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10196BF\"></sup> from Megiddo to Jerusalem and buried him in his own tomb. And the people of the land took Jehoahaz son of Josiah and anointed him and made him king in place of his father.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jehoahaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10197BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10197BH\"></sup> was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem three months. His mother’s name was Hamutal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10197BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10197BI\"></sup> daughter of Jeremiah; she was from Libnah.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10198BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10198BJ\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his predecessors had done.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Pharaoh Necho put him in chains at Riblah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10199BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10199BK\"></sup> in the land of Hamath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10199BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10199BL\"></sup> so that he might not reign in Jerusalem, and he imposed on Judah a levy of a hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Pharaoh Necho made Eliakim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10200BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10200BM\"></sup> son of Josiah king in place of his father Josiah and changed Eliakim’s name to Jehoiakim. But he took Jehoahaz and carried him off to Egypt, and there he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10200BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10200BN\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Jehoiakim paid Pharaoh Necho the silver and gold he demanded. In order to do so, he taxed the land and exacted the silver and gold from the people of the land according to their assessments.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10201BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10201BO\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Jehoiakim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10202BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10202BQ\"></sup> was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eleven years. His mother’s name was Zebidah daughter of Pedaiah; she was from Rumah.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And he did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10203BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10203BR\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his predecessors had done."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>During Jehoiakim’s reign, Nebuchadnezzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10204A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10204A\"></sup> king of Babylon invaded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10204B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10204B\"></sup> the land, and Jehoiakim became his vassal for three years. But then he turned against Nebuchadnezzar and rebelled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10204C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10204C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent Babylonian,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10205D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10205D\"></sup> Aramean,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10205E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10205E\"></sup> Moabite and Ammonite raiders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10205F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10205F\"></sup> against him to destroy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10205G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10205G\"></sup> Judah, in accordance with the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> proclaimed by his servants the prophets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10205H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10205H\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Surely these things happened to Judah according to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s command,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10206I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10206I\"></sup> in order to remove them from his presence<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10206J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10206J\"></sup> because of the sins of Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10206K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10206K\"></sup> and all he had done,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>including the shedding of innocent blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10207L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10207L\"></sup> For he had filled Jerusalem with innocent blood, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not willing to forgive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10207M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10207M\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As for the other events of Jehoiakim’s reign,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10208N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10208N\"></sup> and all he did, are they not written in the book of the annals of the kings of Judah?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Jehoiakim rested<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10209O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10209O\"></sup> with his ancestors. And Jehoiachin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10209P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10209P\"></sup> his son succeeded him as king.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10210Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10210Q\"></sup> did not march out from his own country again, because the king of Babylon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10210R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10210R\"></sup> had taken all his territory, from the Wadi of Egypt to the Euphrates River.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Jehoiachin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10211T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10211T\"></sup> was eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem three months. His mother’s name was Nehushta<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10211U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10211U\"></sup> daughter of Elnathan; she was from Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10212V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10212V\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his father had done.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At that time the officers of Nebuchadnezzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10213W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10213W\"></sup> king of Babylon advanced on Jerusalem and laid siege to it,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Nebuchadnezzar himself came up to the city while his officers were besieging it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jehoiachin king of Judah, his mother, his attendants, his nobles and his officials all surrendered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10215X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10215X\"></sup> to him.In the eighth year of the reign of the king of Babylon, he took Jehoiachin prisoner.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had declared,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10216Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10216Y\"></sup> Nebuchadnezzar removed the treasures<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10216Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10216Z\"></sup> from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and from the royal palace, and cut up the gold articles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10216AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10216AA\"></sup> that Solomon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10216AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10216AB\"></sup> king of Israel had made for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He carried all Jerusalem into exile:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10217AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10217AC\"></sup> all the officers and fighting men,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10217AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10217AD\"></sup> and all the skilled workers and artisans—a total of ten thousand. Only the poorest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10217AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10217AE\"></sup> people of the land were left.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Nebuchadnezzar took Jehoiachin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10218AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10218AF\"></sup> captive to Babylon. He also took from Jerusalem to Babylon the king’s mother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10218AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10218AG\"></sup> his wives, his officials and the prominent people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10218AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10218AH\"></sup> of the land.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The king of Babylon also deported to Babylon the entire force of seven thousand fighting men, strong and fit for war, and a thousand skilled workers and artisans.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10219AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10219AI\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He made Mattaniah, Jehoiachin’s uncle, king in his place and changed his name to Zedekiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10220AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10220AJ\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Zedekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10221AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10221AL\"></sup> was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eleven years. His mother’s name was Hamutal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10221AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10221AM\"></sup> daughter of Jeremiah; she was from Libnah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He did evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10222AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10222AN\"></sup> in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as Jehoiakim had done.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>It was because of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger that all this happened to Jerusalem and Judah, and in the end he thrust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10223AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10223AO\"></sup> them from his presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10223AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10223AP\"></sup>Now Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>So in the ninth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10224A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10224A\"></sup> year of Zedekiah’s reign, on the tenth day of the tenth month, Nebuchadnezzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10224B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10224B\"></sup> king of Babylon marched against Jerusalem with his whole army. He encamped outside the city and built siege works<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10224C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10224C\"></sup> all around it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The city was kept under siege until the eleventh year of King Zedekiah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>By the ninth day of the fourth month the famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10226D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10226D\"></sup> in the city had become so severe that there was no food for the people to eat.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the city wall was broken through,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10227E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10227E\"></sup> and the whole army fled at night through the gate between the two walls near the king’s garden, though the Babylonians were surrounding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10227F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10227F\"></sup> the city. They fled toward the Arabah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>but the Babylonian army pursued the king and overtook him in the plains of Jericho. All his soldiers were separated from him and scattered,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10228G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10228G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and he was captured.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10229H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10229H\"></sup>He was taken to the king of Babylon at Riblah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10229I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10229I\"></sup> where sentence was pronounced on him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They killed the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes. Then they put out his eyes, bound him with bronze shackles and took him to Babylon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10230J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10230J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>On the seventh day of the fifth month, in the nineteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, Nebuzaradan commander of the imperial guard, an official of the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He set fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10232K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10232K\"></sup> to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the royal palace and all the houses of Jerusalem. Every important building he burned down.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10232L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10232L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The whole Babylonian army under the commander of the imperial guard broke down the walls<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10233M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10233M\"></sup> around Jerusalem.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Nebuzaradan the commander of the guard carried into exile<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10234N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10234N\"></sup> the people who remained in the city, along with the rest of the populace and those who had deserted to the king of Babylon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10234O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10234O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the commander left behind some of the poorest people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10235P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10235P\"></sup> of the land to work the vineyards and fields.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The Babylonians broke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10236Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10236Q\"></sup> up the bronze pillars, the movable stands and the bronze Sea that were at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and they carried the bronze to Babylon.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They also took away the pots, shovels, wick trimmers, dishes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10237R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10237R\"></sup> and all the bronze articles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10237S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10237S\"></sup> used in the temple service.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The commander of the imperial guard took away the censers and sprinkling bowls—all that were made of pure gold or silver.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10238T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10238T\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The bronze from the two pillars, the Sea and the movable stands, which Solomon had made for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, was more than could be weighed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Each pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10240U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10240U\"></sup> was eighteen cubits high. The bronze capital on top of one pillar was three cubits high and was decorated with a network and pomegranates of bronze all around. The other pillar, with its network, was similar.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The commander of the guard took as prisoners Seraiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10241V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10241V\"></sup> the chief priest, Zephaniah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10241W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10241W\"></sup> the priest next in rank and the three doorkeepers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10241X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10241X\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Of those still in the city, he took the officer in charge of the fighting men, and five royal advisers. He also took the secretary who was chief officer in charge of conscripting the people of the land and sixty of the conscripts who were found in the city.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Nebuzaradan the commander took them all and brought them to the king of Babylon at Riblah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>There at Riblah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10244Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10244Y\"></sup> in the land of Hamath, the king had them executed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10244Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10244Z\"></sup>So Judah went into captivity,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10244AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10244AA\"></sup> away from her land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10244AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10244AB\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon appointed Gedaliah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10245AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10245AC\"></sup> son of Ahikam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10245AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10245AD\"></sup> the son of Shaphan, to be over the people he had left behind in Judah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When all the army officers and their men heard that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah as governor, they came to Gedaliah at Mizpah—Ishmael son of Nethaniah, Johanan son of Kareah, Seraiah son of Tanhumeth the Netophathite, Jaazaniah the son of the Maakathite, and their men.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Gedaliah took an oath to reassure them and their men. “Do not be afraid of the Babylonian officials,” he said. “Settle down in the land and serve the king of Babylon, and it will go well with you.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In the seventh month, however, Ishmael son of Nethaniah, the son of Elishama, who was of royal blood, came with ten men and assassinated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10248AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10248AE\"></sup> Gedaliah and also the men of Judah and the Babylonians who were with him at Mizpah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10248AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10248AF\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>At this, all the people from the least to the greatest, together with the army officers, fled to Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10249AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10249AG\"></sup> for fear of the Babylonians.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>In the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the year Awel-Marduk became king of Babylon, he released Jehoiachin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10250AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10250AI\"></sup> king of Judah from prison. He did this on the twenty-seventh day of the twelfth month.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He spoke kindly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10251AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10251AJ\"></sup> to him and gave him a seat of honor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10251AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10251AK\"></sup> higher than those of the other kings who were with him in Babylon.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So Jehoiachin put aside his prison clothes and for the rest of his life ate regularly at the king’s table.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10252AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10252AL\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Day by day the king gave Jehoiachin a regular allowance as long as he lived.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10253AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10253AM\"></sup>"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;